1
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:15,080
‎我在澳大利亞的陽光海岸長大
I grew up on the Sunshine Coast in Australia,

2
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:18,290
‎也就是說 ‎我和我的家人從未遠離過大海
which means my family and I were never far from the ocean.

3
00:00:18,370 --> 00:00:20,750
‎我們不是在海里 就是在海上
If we weren't in it, we were on it.

4
00:00:21,330 --> 00:00:23,660
‎我們其實就住在船上 它叫船屋號
We practically lived on our boat, Home Abroad.

5
00:00:24,450 --> 00:00:28,160
‎雖然爸爸媽媽和我們四個孩子 ‎蝸居在里面有點擁擠
It was a tight fit, Mum, Dad, and the four of us kids,

6
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:30,750
‎但只要一家人在一起就很開心
but we were happy because we were together.

7
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:36,830
‎到了晚上 媽媽會給我們講 ‎天上的外星人的故事
At night, Mum would tell us stories about a starman in the sky,

8
00:00:36,910 --> 00:00:39,200
‎還有海浪聲伴我們入眠
then the waves would rock us to sleep.

9
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,750
‎我永遠不會忘記 ‎第一次獨自開船的經歷
I'll never forget the first time I sailed by myself,

10
00:00:44,830 --> 00:00:48,250
‎忘不了當風鼓動船帆時 ‎那油然而生的興奮
the rush of excitement when my sail caught the wind,

11
00:00:48,330 --> 00:00:50,500
‎和大海的神奇魅力
the magic and the allure of the sea.

12
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,330
‎我當上了船長 ‎整個世界展現在我眼前
I was the captain and the whole world was in front of me,

13
00:00:54,410 --> 00:00:56,450
‎等待著被發現
just waiting to be discovered.

14
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,660
‎我能聽到大海在呼喚我的名字
I could hear the ocean calling my name.

15
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:03,040
‎12歲的我 為之深深著迷
By the time I was 12, I was obsessed.

16
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:06,040
‎四年來 我一直在研究海洋和海浪
For four years, I studied the ocean, the waves,

17
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:08,700
‎學習一切關于帆船的知識
and learnt everything I could about sailing boats.

18
00:01:08,790 --> 00:01:11,870
‎我做了三份兼職攢錢
I worked three part-time jobs and saved money,

19
00:01:11,950 --> 00:01:17,040
‎夢想著有朝一日能駕帆船周游世界
because I dreamed that one day I would sail around the world.

20
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:24,540
‎逐夢大海

21
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:24,540
本WEB版外掛字幕由  風吹來的那片云  雙語合并

22
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:36,120
‎（試航 2009年9月 ‎太平洋 澳洲近海）

23
00:03:55,330 --> 00:03:56,790
‎（鮑伊號）

24
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,580
‎杰絲 試航進展如何
Jess, how's the practice run going?

25
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:10,790
‎剛被一艘突然出現的貨船撞了
Cargo ship hit me. Came out of nowhere.

26
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:11,910
‎船進水了嗎
You taking on water?

27
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,620
‎沒有 看上去沒漏水 但桅桿斷了
No. No, doesn't look like it, but I've been dismasted.

28
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:18,080
‎為什么警報沒響
Why didn't the alarm go off?

29
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,790
‎把你的坐標給我
Okay, give me your coordinates.

30
00:04:22,910 --> 00:04:25,540
‎南緯26度 25…
Uh, we're at 26 degrees, 25…

31
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,620
‎杰絲 穩住呼吸
Jess, breathe.

32
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,000
‎集中精神
Focus.

33
00:04:57,370 --> 00:04:58,950
‎天啊 出什么事了
Oh, my God, what happened?

34
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:02,370
‎她沒事 跟一艘貨船撞了
She's okay. Collided with a cargo ship.

35
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,830
‎她被貨船撞了
She was hit by a cargo ship?

36
00:05:04,910 --> 00:05:05,950
‎酷啊
Cool.

37
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,200
‎一點也不酷 湯姆
Not cool, Tom.

38
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,200
‎她不會有事吧
Is she gonna be all right?

39
00:05:09,290 --> 00:05:12,120
‎-她一定不會有事的 回去睡覺 ‎-想得美
-I'm sure she'll be fine. Go back to bed. -As if.

40
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:17,620
‎杰絲 你受傷了嗎
Jess, are you hurt?

41
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,330
‎沒有 媽媽 我沒事
No, Mum, I'm fine.

42
00:05:20,540 --> 00:05:22,080
‎真的 我保證
Really, I promise.

43
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:29,000
‎我們說好了的 不能撞上任何東西
Thought we agreed, no collisions.

44
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,290
‎我也不想啊
I couldn't help myself.

45
00:05:30,370 --> 00:05:32,450
‎我能跟杰絲說話嗎 我想跟杰絲聊
Can I talk to Jess? I want to talk to Jess!

46
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:34,540
‎-讓我說幾句吧  ‎-等漢娜說完
-Oh, can I talk to her? -I haven't talked to her.

47
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:37,700
‎-那是海盜船嗎  ‎-她把坐標報錯了
-Jess, was it a pirate ship? -She's getting her coordinates wrong.

48
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:39,370
‎我要呼叫海岸警衛隊
Okay, come on. That's it. -I'm calling the Coast Guard.

49
00:05:39,450 --> 00:05:42,040
‎別 會有一堆記者涌過來的
-Don't. Reporters will be lining the docks.

50
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:45,580
‎他們都等著看她失敗呢 ‎她不能一瘸一拐地回來
They are waiting for her to fail. She cannot come limping back in.

51
00:05:45,660 --> 00:05:48,370
‎-你確定她的船還適合航海嗎  ‎-她認為可以
-Do we know if the boat's seaworthy? -She reckons it is.

52
00:05:48,450 --> 00:05:52,790
‎-那個16歲的姑娘… ‎-杰絲需要確認她能獨立完成行程
-Oh, well, as long as the 16-year-old-- -Jess needs to know she can do this alone.

53
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:55,580
‎她離海岸只有32公里
She's only 20 miles from the shore.

54
00:05:56,540 --> 00:06:00,450
‎想象一下 如果這時候 ‎她離最近的港口也有3200公里呢
Now imagine if she does this, and she's 2,000 miles from the nearest port.

55
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:04,200
‎我們會在碼頭等你 ‎也許情況沒那么糟
We'll be at the marina to meet you. It's probably not that bad in daylight.

56
00:06:04,290 --> 00:06:05,540
‎謝謝你 艾米莉
Thanks, Em.

57
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,080
‎杰絲
Jess!

58
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:25,160
‎好了 聽到我說“迎風轉向”
Okay, so when I say tack,

59
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,950
‎我們就把帆轉向另一邊
we're gonna switch the sail to the other side.

60
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,080
‎準備好贏了嗎
You ready to win?

61
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:31,540
‎好了 我們開始吧
All right, guys, let's get started!

62
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:41,870
‎-嘿 杰絲 怎么了  ‎-我還沒準備好
Hey! Jess, what's wrong? -I'm not ready.

63
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:43,330
‎-沒有嗎  ‎-親愛的
-No? -Oh, sweetheart.

64
00:06:43,830 --> 00:06:46,540
‎-你不想去了  ‎-還沒做好心理準備
-Don't want to go, kiddo? I think we're still finding our sea legs.

65
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:49,580
‎-好吧 ‎-我聽說你是奪冠熱門呢
-Fair enough. -Well, I heard you're the favorite to win.

66
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:52,290
‎是啊 也許吧
Yeah. Maybe.

67
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:54,330
‎來呀 杰絲
Come on, Jess!

68
00:06:54,410 --> 00:06:57,120
‎不試試怎么知道 ‎海上是怎樣的景象呢
You won't know what's out there unless you try.

69
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,910
‎別跑太遠
No, no, not too far.

70
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,250
‎等等 艾米莉
Wait, Emily, wait!

71
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,540
‎快來 杰絲
Quick, Jess!

72
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,950
‎過來 好了
Come here. There you go.

73
00:07:19,330 --> 00:07:23,410
‎杰西卡沃森唯一的試航提早結束 ‎證明反對她此行的人…
Jessica Watson's only sea trial has been cut short, proving her critics…

74
00:07:25,910 --> 00:07:28,830
‎阿瑟頓 嘿 阿瑟頓
Atherton! Hey, Atherton!

75
00:07:29,410 --> 00:07:31,410
‎他怎么就能過去
How come he's allowed down there?

76
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,160
‎-阿瑟頓 ‎-本
-Atherton. -Ben.

77
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:39,750
‎你們這幫人來這里干什么
Don't know what you lot think you're doing here.

78
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:42,120
‎我們來是因為…
Well, I guess we're here because…

79
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,080
‎（警察-粉紅號）

80
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:47,660
‎…居然有人要讓一個孩子 ‎開著一艘那么小的船出海
that boat is a shockingly tiny thing to send a child out to sea in.

81
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:49,950
‎-不光小 還很脆弱 ‎-別理他了
-It's pretty flimsy too. -Leave it.

82
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:51,580
‎趁火打劫的家伙
Vultures.

83
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,450
‎那就別讓他們得逞
Then don't feed them.

84
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,870
‎為什么不讓得逞
Why aren't we feeding vultures?

85
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,620
‎你姐姐嘗試做的事
It's not every day that someone

86
00:07:57,700 --> 00:08:00,580
‎很少有像她這么年輕的人會去做
as young as your sister tries to do what she's doing.

87
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:03,330
‎這是一件大事 人們會有疑問
It's a big deal. People have questions, that's all.

88
00:08:03,410 --> 00:08:04,790
‎這令她成了關注的焦點
Plus, it makes her a target.

89
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:08,290
‎成功了 就把她捧成英雄 ‎失敗了 悲劇故事也能大賣
If she succeeds, she's a hero. If she fails, well, tragedy sells.

90
00:08:09,370 --> 00:08:10,500
‎她才十歲啊
She's ten.

91
00:08:16,410 --> 00:08:19,750
‎他們在尋找弱點 別讓他們輕慢了你
They're looking for weakness. Don't let 'em treat you any different.

92
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:22,500
‎你是一名船長 明白嗎
You're a captain, got it?

93
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:36,660
‎好的 我是杰西卡的顧問 本布萊恩特
All right, I'm Ben Bryant, Jessica's advisor.

94
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:38,000
‎杰絲
Jess.

95
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:40,330
‎我是杰西卡沃森
I-- I'm Jessica Watson.

96
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:46,500
‎我計劃成為全世界最年輕的獨自完成
And, uh, I… I'm planning on being the youngest person

97
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:49,080
‎無間斷環球航海之旅的人
to sail around the world nonstop and unassisted.

98
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,620
‎昨晚發生了什么事
Jessica, what happened last night?

99
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:52,830
‎-發生了碰撞 ‎-是你的錯嗎
-There was a collision. -Were you at fault?

100
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,790
‎一艘貨船偏離了它的航道
A cargo ship detoured from its route.

101
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:58,830
‎杰西卡 ‎這是你唯一一次試航的第一夜
Jessica, this was night one of your only test run.

102
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:02,450
‎你無法平安在兩個港口之間往返 ‎又如何環游世界呢
How are you gonna make it around the world if you can't make it between two ports?

103
00:09:02,540 --> 00:09:04,700
‎本 我們不是來聽你說話的 謝謝
Uh, and we're not here for you. Thanks, Ben.

104
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:07,330
‎我相信我可以
I believe I can.

105
00:09:07,410 --> 00:09:09,120
‎你明白你要做的是什么嗎
You understand what you're in for?

106
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:14,540
‎那可是汪洋大海啊 ‎海浪有公寓樓那么高
Uh, we're talking open ocean, waves the size of apartment buildings,

107
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:15,750
‎風速130公里每小時
70-knot winds.

108
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:18,580
‎這就是航海界的珠穆朗瑪峰
I mean, this is the Mount Everest of sailing.

109
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:21,450
‎對 航線確實頗有挑戰性
Well, yes, the-- the route is challenging,

110
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:23,750
‎但我半輩子都在航海 所以我…
but, uh, I've sailed half my life, so I--

111
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:25,040
‎也就是只有幾年嘍
So a couple years then?

112
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:29,330
‎我已經完成了 ‎18520公里的里程數 我有資格
I've done the 10,000 nautical miles. I'm qualified.

113
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,120
‎而且我們做足了準備
And we've prepared.

114
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:34,080
‎她怎么能想到 ‎會有貨船連航海雷達都不看
How could she prepare for a cargo ship that ignores its radar?

115
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:37,830
‎那為什么在撞擊之前 ‎你的感應警報器沒向你示警
So why didn't your proximity alarms alert you before the crash?

116
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:42,500
‎我忘記把它打開了
-I forgot to turn them on.

117
00:09:44,830 --> 00:09:47,660
‎沃森先生 沃森太太 ‎你們想必無法認同此種行為吧
Mr. and Mrs. Watson, surely you have reservations hearing that?

118
00:09:48,830 --> 00:09:52,200
‎她犯了一個錯誤 我相信她不會再犯
She made a mistake. It's one I'm certain she won't make again.

119
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:54,160
‎你們不認為16歲太年輕了嗎
So you don't think 16 is too young?

120
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:56,750
‎我們憑什么否定她的夢想
Who are we to deny her her dreams?

121
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:59,750
‎她一直為之努力奮斗 ‎也證明了她有這個實力
She's worked hard and proven she can do this every step of the way.

122
00:09:59,830 --> 00:10:02,160
‎那么 新的啟航日定在哪一天
So when is the new departure day?

123
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:05,660
‎我想應該在十月中旬之前出發吧
Uh, well, I guess we just have to leave by mid-October.

124
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:09,330
‎也就是兩周后 很樂觀啊 不是嗎
So two weeks. Hmm, optimistic, no?

125
00:10:09,410 --> 00:10:12,950
‎那是南冰洋布滿冰山之前的 ‎最后一個窗口期
Well, it's the last window before the Southern Ocean's filled with icebergs.

126
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:13,950
‎杰西卡
Jessica!

127
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:16,410
‎如果官方讓你取消計劃呢
Well, what about calls by authorities to cancel altogether?

128
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:19,040
‎本 你有能力 ‎讓這個女孩平安回家嗎
Ben, are you the right person to bring this girl home?

129
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,410
‎我有經驗
Got a bit of experience.

130
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:23,620
‎但你在千禧杯比賽擔任船長時 ‎就曾失去一名船員
But as captain in the Millennium Cup, you lost one of your own crew members.

131
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:24,950
‎馬特特納
A Matt Turner.

132
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,500
‎嘿 夠了
Hey! That's enough.

133
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:28,830
‎-請讓我說完… ‎-不 我們聽夠了
-Well, let me finish-- -Nah. We're done here.

134
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:36,450
‎四年的努力換來這滿目瘡痍
Four years of hard work boils down to this.

135
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:39,330
‎我有查看航海雷達 但沒看見那艘船
Ben, I looked at the radar and I didn't see the ship.

136
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:41,830
‎我就是打了個盹兒 沒想到…
And it was just a short nap. So I didn't think that--

137
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:44,830
‎不 你根本沒有思考 ‎這是不負責任的行為 杰絲
No, you didn't think. It was irresponsible, Jess.

138
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:47,450
‎而且你老是報錯坐標
You know you kept getting your coordinates wrong too?

139
00:10:49,290 --> 00:10:51,580
‎你的精神狀態至關重要
It's your state of mind that matters out there.

140
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:55,410
‎如果被閱讀障礙影響了判斷 ‎你會在大海中迷失的
If dyslexia takes over, you are lost in the middle of the ocean, mate.

141
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,410
‎好了 我們明白了
All right. All right, we get it.

142
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,580
‎你覺得我們能修好它嗎
Do you reckon we can fix it?

143
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:06,450
‎雖然狀況有點慘烈 但沒問題
Bit of a dog's breakfast, but… -Yeah,

144
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,370
‎它還有得救
there's some life left in her yet.

145
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:10,750
‎不過 修繕它是個大工程
I mean, these aren't small repairs, though.

146
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,700
‎我們既沒錢又沒人力 ‎也沒有合適的維修地點
We've got no money, no manpower, no location to even fix it.

147
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:16,620
‎不能找我的贊助人出資嗎
Yeah, but won't my sponsors help?

148
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:20,080
‎之前就換過一次桅桿 ‎不知道這回他們還愿不愿買單
Not sure they'll want to pay for a new mast twice over.

149
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:25,160
