00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:02,830
‎他們就愛多管閑事
They can't help themselves.

181
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:07,080
‎一個孩子沒有能力理解其中的風險
A child does not have the ability to understand the risks involved.

182
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:09,790
‎他們就沒其它 ‎更有意義的事可討論了嗎
You'd think they'd have something bloody better to talk about.

183
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:14,290
‎所有人都有一個疑問 ‎“杰西卡沃森是否太年輕了
The question on everyone's lips, "Is Jessica Watson too young,

184
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:17,160
‎以及 她的父母為何沒有加以制止 ”
and where are her parents in all of this?"

185
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:20,500
‎這令人不得不懷疑這究竟 ‎是杰西卡的夢想 還是她父母的
You do have to wonder if this is Jessica's dream or theirs.

186
00:13:20,580 --> 00:13:24,120
‎社交媒體上也在議論 ‎他們說我們是“粗野的海盜”
It's on social media too. They're calling us "bogan pirates."

187
00:13:25,410 --> 00:13:27,660
‎拜托 太好笑了
Oh, come on, that's great.

188
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,160
‎我要寫一個評論
Let me write a comment!

189
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:30,830
‎-不行 漢娜 ‎-不行
-No, Hannah. -No, Hanna, no.

190
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:33,660
‎昆士蘭政府正起草法案
The Queensland government is working on a bill

191
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:37,410
‎援引兒童福利政策 ‎意圖阻止杰西卡出海
to stop Jessica from sailing, citing child welfare.

192
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,700
‎他們不能這么做 他們可以嗎
They can't do that! Can they?

193
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:51,370
‎您所撥打的用戶無法接通 ‎請稍后再撥
The person you are calling is unavailable. Please try again.

194
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,330
‎應該沒那么糟吧
It can't be that bad.

195
00:13:58,410 --> 00:14:01,040
‎沒那么糟 只是禍不單行而已
Oh, no. No, just everything's falling apart.

196
00:14:01,950 --> 00:14:03,160
‎棚屋都訂滿了
Sheds are booked up.

197
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:07,250
‎我沒錢雇人幫忙 沒錢買零件 ‎贊助人也沒有任何回應
Can't afford help or parts, and now, none of my sponsors are responding.

198
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:09,620
‎你得給他們點兒時間
You have to give them a minute.

199
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:11,160
‎我沒時間了
I don't have time.

200
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,080
‎我猜他們一定在看新聞
I bet they're watching the news.

201
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:20,000
‎-所有人都說我做不到 ‎-誰在乎啊
-Everyone's saying I can't do it. -Who cares?

202
00:14:20,830 --> 00:14:23,580
‎-你有信心就行 ‎-除非我能及時把小粉修好
-You think you can. -Only if I get Pink fixed in time.

203
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,790
‎我知道事情的進展不如預期
I know things aren't going according to plan,

204
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:35,000
這很令人沮喪
‎and… I know how frustrating that is.

205
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:39,870
‎但正是在出現差錯時 ‎你真實的品質才會展現出來
But it's when things go wrong that your true character's revealed.

206
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:44,830
‎現在在我眼前的 ‎是一個強大 堅定 頑強的姑娘
And right now, I'm looking at a strong, committed, tenacious young woman

207
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:47,370
‎她一定能解決面臨的問題
who will figure this out.

208
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,120
‎其余時候我都沒有這些品質嗎
So I'm not those things the rest of the time?

209
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,870
‎不 其余時候你就是個噩夢
No, the rest of the time you're an absolute nightmare.

210
00:14:54,950 --> 00:14:56,120
‎是啊
Yeah.

211
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:01,660
‎只要你堅持不懈 ‎就能克服一切困難 杰絲
You can overcome anything if you keep working at it, Jess.

212
00:15:03,410 --> 00:15:05,330
‎我已經見證過這一點了
I've watched you do it before.

213
00:15:10,370 --> 00:15:12,200
‎（正如磁鐵的兩極一樣）

214
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:16,160
‎我做不到
It's impossible.

215
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:19,450
‎我們來試試你更感興趣的題材吧
Let's try something a little more up your alley.

216
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:22,700
‎色彩會幫你集中注意力 再試一次
The colors will help you focus. Try again.

217
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:30,370
‎杰西馬丁 最年輕的
"Jesse Martin, the youngest person

218
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:32,370
‎獨自航海
to s-- sail solo

219
00:15:32,950 --> 00:15:35,000
‎環游世界的人
ar-- around the world."

220
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,250
‎環游整個世界
Around the whole world?

221
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:39,750
‎還能做這種事
You can do that?

222
00:15:48,790 --> 00:15:52,080
‎我做了全面檢查 計算過成本
I did a full inspection and I got costs.

223
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:55,620
‎我們需要一根新桅桿 ‎還要更換索具 修補船體
And we'll need a new mast, new rigging, hull repairs.

224
00:15:57,250 --> 00:15:59,790
‎應該只會稍微推遲一下
That is just a slight delay, I reckon.

225
00:15:59,870 --> 00:16:02,620
‎只要我趕在11月之前出海就好
As long as I'm on the ocean before November.

226
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,950
‎-嘿 別神游了  ‎-什么
-Hello, Earth to Ben! -What?

227
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:06,870
‎拜托 我是認真的
Come on, Ben, I'm serious.

228
00:16:06,950 --> 00:16:09,370
‎我們還能成行 來得及修好小粉…
We can still do this. -There's still time to fix up Pink--

229
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:10,290
‎我知道
‎-I know.

230
00:16:11,540 --> 00:16:12,370
‎你要來嗎
-You coming?

231
00:16:14,290 --> 00:16:15,290
‎去哪兒
Where to?

232
00:16:17,830 --> 00:16:19,370
‎有東西給你看
Got something to show you.

233
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,540
‎-本 我不想要另一艘船 ‎-對
-Ben, I don't want another boat. -Yep.

234
00:16:30,620 --> 00:16:32,870
‎我和小粉是一個團隊 我了解小粉
Pink and I are a team. I know Pink.

235
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,080
‎它鬧脾氣
I know when she's angry.

236
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:36,290
‎-或者出問題了 我都能知道 ‎-對
-I know when she's in trouble. -Yeah.

237
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:57,250
‎召集了一些幫手
Rounded up a bit of assistance.

238
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,250
‎自從媒體開始攻擊你
Once the media attacked you,

239
00:16:59,330 --> 00:17:01,500
‎他們就自告奮勇來幫忙了 ‎我攔都攔不住
I couldn't stop 'em from volunteering to help.

240
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:02,950
‎為什么
Why?

241
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:06,410
‎因為媒體攻擊了我們自己人啊
Well, media went after one of our own.

242
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:09,950
‎雖然你要單獨出海 ‎但你現在也是有組織的人了
You might be sailing solo, but you belong to a tribe now.

243
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:13,790
‎我們趕在法案通過前 助你下水吧
This gets you on the water before they pass this blasted bill.

244
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:21,040
‎-你不是在做夢 杰絲 看看身后 ‎-她來啦
-It's all real, Jess. Look behind you. -She's here!

245
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:28,200
‎漢娜 什么也別碰 不行
Oi, Hannah, don't touch anything! No!

246
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:31,500
‎來吧
Come on!

247
00:17:40,870 --> 00:17:42,700
‎布給我 謝了 伙計
Cloth? Thanks, mate.

248
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:48,040
‎好的 請稍等
Okay, just a sec.

249
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:57,080
‎對 是一 二 三 四
Right, it's one, two, three, four.

250
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,500
‎湯姆
Tom!

251
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,200
‎（我會一直想你哦 ‎艾米莉）

252
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:09,450
‎（廁所）

253
00:18:18,950 --> 00:18:24,250
‎（敢于夢想）

254
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:40,910
‎嘿 羅杰 兄弟 有個小問題
Hey, Roger. -Rog, mate, just a quick question.

255
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:50,200
‎（粉紅號）

256
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,200
‎嘿 小粉
Hey, Pink.

257
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,040
‎歡迎回來
Welcome back.

258
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:07,410
‎-別鬧  ‎-淡定
-No! -Easy, easy!

259
00:19:09,410 --> 00:19:11,500
‎他們就不能消停一天嗎
Can't they take a break for one day?

260
00:19:11,580 --> 00:19:14,120
‎阻止杰西卡的呼聲越來越高
And calls to stop Jessica only grow.

261
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:16,870
‎就連她父親 ‎今日早些時候也表達了疑慮
Even her father expressed doubt earlier today.

262
00:19:16,950 --> 00:19:19,830
‎羅杰 你對杰絲撞船一事感想如何
Rog! Man, how are you feeling about Jess's collision?

263
00:19:19,910 --> 00:19:24,370
‎任何青少年出了這種事 ‎都會讓人擔心吧
Well, uh, you know, any teen crashing their vehicle doesn't exactly fill you with confidence, does it?

264
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:29,540
‎-說好的不回應媒體呢  ‎-我就是開個玩笑
What happened to not talking to the media? It was a joke.

265
00:19:29,620 --> 00:19:33,580
‎-在國家電視臺上開的玩笑 ‎-他斷章取義了 知道嗎
That you made on national TV. Uh, he took it out of context, you know?

266
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:36,580
‎-你覺得我做不到嗎  ‎-什么
-Do you think I can't do it? -What?

267
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,080
我不知道
‎I don't know.

268
00:19:40,830 --> 00:19:44,540
‎其實我之前以為 ‎你只是一時頭腦發熱 過一個月
To be honest, I thought this would be something you'd fixate on for a month

269
00:19:44,620 --> 00:19:46,910
‎-就會拋諸腦后呢 ‎-別說了
and then you'd get over it. Rog, stop.

270
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:50,950
‎對不起
I'm sorry.

271
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,830
‎你不希望我去嗎
Do you wish I wasn't going?

272
00:19:57,660 --> 00:19:58,500
‎嘿
Hey.

273
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:01,540
‎聽我說 好嗎
You listen to me, all right?

274
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:05,450
‎我希望你能實現所有的夢想
I want you to achieve everything that you aspire to.

275
00:20:06,660 --> 00:20:07,580
‎但…
But…

276
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:11,080
‎你是我的寶貝女兒啊
you're my little girl.

277
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:13,080
‎對嗎
Yeah?

278
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:16,870
‎對
Yeah.

279
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:21,080
‎杰絲
Jess.

280
00:20:25,950 --> 00:20:27,200
‎別吐槽我
Hey. Don't you start.

281
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:29,950
‎可惡
Damn it.

282
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:39,910
‎你知道他不是那個意思 ‎他只是害怕了
You know he doesn't mean it. He's just scared.

283
00:20:41,620 --> 00:20:44,580
‎不 也許那些記者是對的
Maybe the journo's right, No.

284
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:48,500
‎也許我就該知難而退 ‎溜出去派對狂歡
maybe I should just… quit, and sneak out to parties.

285
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:51,500
‎相信我 ‎老爸絕對也不喜歡你干那種事
Dad definitely doesn't like that either. Trust me.

286
00:20:54,410 --> 00:20:57,120
‎要知道 總會有人評頭論足
You know, people are always gonna have opinions

287
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,250
‎談論你該做什么 不該做什么的
on what you should and shouldn't be doing.

288
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:02,500
‎我見過你航海時有多開心
But I see how happy you are when you sail,

289
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:05,250
‎所以為了你自己 去吧
so just do it for you.

290
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:07,540
‎你真睿智
You're very wise.

291
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:10,700
‎好了 驚喜時間
All right. Surprise time.

292
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:11,620
‎好吧
-Okay.

293
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:17,370
‎我為你這趟旅程建了一個博客
I set up a blog for your trip.

294
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:19,620
‎-什么  ‎-別擔心 我會負責打理
-What? -Don't worry. I'll run it.

295
00:21:21,330 --> 00:21:23,080
‎這樣每個人都能聽見你的聲音了
Then everyone can hear your voice,

296
00:21:23,950 --> 00:21:27,500
‎我認為它有時候值得聆聽
'cause I think it's worth listening to. Sometimes.

297
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:34,370
‎謝謝你 艾米莉
Thanks, Em.

298
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,080
‎巧克力餅干
Tim Tam?

299
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,450
‎好的 我熱身完畢了
Okay, I'm warmed up.

300
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:46,540
‎-你們準備好了嗎 三 二 一 ‎-開拍
-You guys good? Three, two, one. -Rolling.

301
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,910
‎這一天終于來了
And the day has finally come.

302
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:52,080
‎再過幾個小時 幾經波折之后
In just a few hours and after several setbacks,

303
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:56,500
‎杰西卡沃森即將干勁十足地 ‎開啟她的獨自航海之旅
Jessica Watson is set to embark on her solo voyage,

304
00:21:56,580 --> 00:21:59,910
‎不顧反對者們的聲音 ‎搶在政府法案頒布前出發
ignoring her critics and outrunning the government bill.

305
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:03,620
‎這個好 把這段加進新聞詞
Whoo! That's the one. Print that.

306
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:07,500
‎給 好的 謝了 親愛的
There you go. Yeah, thanks, darling.

307
00:22:12,910 --> 00:22:14,500
‎孤單時就抱抱它吧
For when you get lonely.

308
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:18,120
‎我不能帶走科比考拉熊 ‎它是你的最愛
No, I can't take Kobi Koala. She's your favorite.

309
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,040
‎對
Yeah.

310
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:21,620
‎所以只是暫時借給你
That's why she's just on loan.

311
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:22,540
‎好嗎
Okay?

312
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:26,080
‎我保證一定把它安全帶回家
All right, then I promise to bring her home safe, yeah?

313
00:22:34,410 --> 00:22:36,830
‎-好了 速戰速決吧 ‎-是啊
-All right, fast and quick. -Yeah.

314
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:42,290
‎為了擺脫家庭作業 ‎你也是豁出去了啊
Doing an awful lot to get out of homework.

315
00:22:45,370 --> 00:22:47,620
‎再見 湯姆 好了
Bye, Tom. All right.

316
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,540
‎我打包了你要的巧克力 ‎別一口氣吃完
-So I packed the chocolate you asked for. -Don't eat it all in one go, all right?

317
00:22:58,620 --> 00:22:59,620
‎謝謝你 爸爸
-Thanks, Dad.

318
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:02,540
‎每天給我打兩次電話 ‎匯報你所在的經緯度
I want you to call and give me your longs and lats twice a day.

319
00:23:02,620 --> 00:23:03,700
‎為什么
Why?

320
00:23:03,790 --> 00:23:06,080
‎如果報錯了 我就能知道你壓力很大
Because if you get them wrong, I'll know you're stressed.

321
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,870
‎利用閱讀障礙來監視我
Using dyslexia to spy on me?

322
00:23:07,950 --> 00:23:10,750
‎沒錯 無論如何都不能漏打 好吧
Yeah, that's right. -No buts, all right?

323
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,200
‎你沒問題的
You'll be all right.

324
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:25,080
‎嘿
Hey.

325
00:23:28,290 --> 00:23:32,080
‎要看日落 慶祝你的重大突破哦
celebrate the milestones, and… don't forget to dance in the rain.

326
00:23:32,830 --> 00:23:34,830
‎還有 在雨中跳舞
Watch the sunsets,

327
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:39,580
‎一定要平安回來 好嗎
You come back home safe, okay?

328
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:50,410
‎你覺得它準備好了嗎
Do you think she's ready?

329
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:52,750
‎只有一個辦法能知道
Only one way to find out.

330
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:57,540
‎這是我首次航海時的護身符
It's a good luck charm from my first nav.

331
00:23:59,870 --> 00:24:02,080
‎總能保我平安回來 現在歸你了
Always brought me back. It's yours now.

332
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:04,000
‎-本 我不能收 ‎-你能
-Ben, I can't. -'Course you can.

333
00:24:08,580 --> 00:24:10,000
‎去吧 出海去吧
Go on. Get out of here.

334
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,000
‎-再見  ‎-再見 杰絲
Bye, Jess!

335
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:29,000
‎-再見 杰絲  ‎-再見 杰絲

336
00:24:34,870 --> 00:24:35,870
‎祝你好運
Good luck!

337
00:24:36,620 --> 00:24:37,620
‎再見
Bye!

338
00:24:41,450 --> 00:24:42,540
‎她不會有事的
She'll be okay.

339
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:11,370
‎（粉紅女士）

340
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:14,200
‎（粉紅號）

341
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:35,160
‎好了
All right.

342
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:41,040
‎她到達起點了
There she is, starting now.

343
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:43,500
‎（官方出發線）

344
00:25:43,580 --> 00:25:45,200
‎4點13分
-Four-point-one-three?

345
00:25:45,290 --> 00:25:46,540
‎4點13分
-Four-point-one-three.

346
00:25:55,540 --> 00:26:02,540
‎（第一天 悉尼港 ‎2009年10月18日）

347
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:32,330
‎好啦 小粉
Oh, whoa! All right, Pink!

348
00:27:14,910 --> 00:27:17,370
‎-你真惡心  ‎-我嘴里都塞滿了
-Ew, you're disgusting! -My mouth is full.

349
00:27:19,410 --> 00:27:21,660
‎好了 大伙兒聽我說
Okay, so listen up.

350
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:25,500
‎本同意在這里追蹤杰絲的動向
Ben's agreed to work in here while, uh, he's tracking Jess,

351
00:27:25,580 --> 00:27:27,250
‎給他騰個地方出來
so just give him a bit of space, all right?

352
00:27:31,870 --> 00:27:33,500
‎做夢吧你…
In your dreams…

353
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:38,500
‎這是什么
What is all this stuff?

354
00:27:38,580 --> 00:27:40,120
‎什么都別碰
Don't touch anything.

355
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,700
‎-那你也別碰我的麥片 ‎-行吧
-Then don't touch my Weet-Bix. -Fine.

356
00:27:43,290 --> 00:27:44,120
‎行吧
-Fine.

357
00:27:45,870 --> 00:27:46,790
‎好了
All right.

358
00:27:57,500 --> 00:27:59,120
‎-是杰西卡的電話嗎  ‎-我來接
-Is that Jessica? -I got it! I got it.

359
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,410
‎我來 嘿 伙計
-Mine, mine, mine! Hey, mate.

360
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:06,950
‎南緯27度33分 東經170度30分
27 degrees, 33 minutes south, and 170 degrees, 30 minutes east.

361
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:08,870
‎正確
-Spot on.

362
00:28:09,370 --> 00:28:13,200
‎-補給情況如何 充足嗎  ‎-爸 我這才剛出發
How are the supplies, do you have enough? Dad, I only just left.

363
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:15,620
別 朱莉…天吶…
‎Oh, no, Jules! Oh, my--

364
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:17,620
‎杰絲
Jess!

365
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:19,200
‎嗨 媽媽
Hi, Mum!

366
00:28:20,830 --> 00:28:21,950
‎出海的感覺如何
How's it feel out there?

367
00:28:23,870 --> 00:28:25,250
‎不枉我苦等這么久
Worth the wait.

368
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,330
‎把繩子拋過來
Chuck the rope.

369
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:45,540
‎交給我吧
I got it.

370
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:49,790
‎快扔呀
Just do it!

371
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:10,580
‎我技術可還行
Is that acceptable?

372
00:29:10,660 --> 00:29:12,620
‎行 謝了 孩子
Yep. Thanks, kid.

373
00:29:13,910 --> 00:29:17,120
‎他們都覺得我瘦弱 年紀小 ‎什么事都做不了
No one thinks I'm big or strong enough to do anything.

374
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,160
‎但我可以
But I am!

375
00:29:19,250 --> 00:29:21,370
‎我一直在練習
I practice all the time, whenever I get the chance.

376
00:29:22,410 --> 00:29:25,040
‎你不必向我證明任何事 伙計
You don't have to prove anything to me, mate.

377
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,370
‎但身為女孩子 我不得不證明自己
Well, that's what girls have to do.

378
00:29:28,790 --> 00:29:30,700
‎你是本布萊恩特嗎
Are you Ben Bryant?

379
00:29:31,500 --> 00:29:33,450
‎-不是 ‎-你是
-No. -Yes, you are.

380
00:29:33,540 --> 00:29:37,450
‎你在南極洲航行時 ‎失去了小拇指的指尖
You lost the tip of your pinky finger sailing in Antarctica.

381
00:29:40,410 --> 00:29:41,500
‎沒有失去
I didn't lose it.

382
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:45,370
‎-我把它放在抽屜里了 ‎-好吧
-I put it in the drawer. -Cool.

383
00:29:46,580 --> 00:29:51,250
‎你12次從悉尼航行到霍巴特 ‎三次單人出海繞澳大利亞航行
You've done 12 Sydney to Hobarts and circumnavigated solo three times.

384
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,500
‎單人航海好玩嗎
Is solo sailing good?

385
00:29:53,580 --> 00:29:55,290
‎是啊 可好玩了
Yeah, it's great.

386
00:29:55,370 --> 00:29:56,830
‎沒人跟你說話
No one talks to you.

387
00:29:58,580 --> 00:30:01,000
‎我想積累經驗 好出海環游世界
I'm trying to get experience so I can sail the world,

388
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:02,870
‎但沒人給我機會
but no one's giving me a chance to.

389
00:30:03,830 --> 00:30:07,120
‎那就自己創造機會
So? Make your own chance.

390
00:30:11,830 --> 00:30:13,540
‎嗨 我是杰絲
Hi, I'm Jess.

391
00:30:13,620 --> 00:30:15,040
‎歡迎觀看我的視頻日志
Welcome to my video log!

392
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:16,870
‎傳統的做法是 水手們會寫日志
Traditionally, sailors keep log books,

393
00:30:16,950 --> 00:30:19,580
‎但我可不要被剝奪半年的螢幕時間
but you can't deprive me of screen time for half a year.

394
00:30:20,330 --> 00:30:22,660
‎不過 大概只有我媽會看這個吧
I'm sure it'll just be my mum watching, though.

395
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,160
‎嗨 媽媽
‎Hi, Mum!

396
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:27,750
‎我帶你參觀一下我未來七個月的家吧
I thought I'd give you a tour of my home for the next seven months,

397
00:30:28,330 --> 00:30:29,450
‎那么…
so…

398
00:30:30,540 --> 00:30:33,040
‎這是我的廚房 我會在這兒做飯
Here's my kitchen where I'll be cooking.

399
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:37,750
‎這是導航臺 ‎我在這里操控所有電器和通訊設備
And here is the nav table where I control all the electrics and communication.

400
00:30:37,830 --> 00:30:40,410
‎我的床鋪 我在這兒睡覺
Uh, my berth, where I'll sleep.

401
00:30:42,410 --> 00:30:43,410
‎廁所
Dunny.

402
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:46,160
‎這里是存放食物的地方
Uh, and this is where all my food is.

403
00:30:46,950 --> 00:30:48,500
‎比如…
For example…

404
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:52,200
‎天吶 凍干西蘭花
Oh, my God, freeze-dried broccoli.

405
00:30:54,410 --> 00:30:56,120
‎（巧克力 ‎吃過西蘭花才能吃 ）

406
00:30:56,950 --> 00:30:58,160
‎干得漂亮 爸爸
Nice one, Dad.

407
00:30:59,250 --> 00:31:01,620
‎我會獨自駕船連續行駛
So I'll be sailing unassisted and nonstop.

408
00:31:01,700 --> 00:31:03,950
‎如果停靠港口 就會被取消資格
So if I pull into port, I'm disqualified.

409
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:07,540
‎我必須航行穿過所有經線 ‎繞過全部四個海岬
And I have to cross all lines of longitude and round all four capes

410
00:31:07,620 --> 00:31:10,120
‎才能算真正完成了環球航海
for it to count as a true circumnavigation.

411
00:31:10,700 --> 00:31:12,370
‎這是我的預計航線
Here's what I'll be doing.

412
00:31:12,450 --> 00:31:14,040
‎這里是悉尼
Okay, here's Sydney.

413
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:16,330
‎往東北走 越過赤道
Going northeast, up past the equator,

414
00:31:16,410 --> 00:31:19,700
‎然后南下 繞過智利南端的合恩角
then back down south to round Cape Horn at the tip of Chile,

415
00:31:19,790 --> 00:31:25,080
‎繼而橫渡大西洋 前往南非的好望角
then across the Atlantic Ocean to the Cape of Good Hope in South Africa,

416
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:31,000
‎接著穿過印度洋 ‎到澳洲西部的露紋角
then over the Indian Ocean to Cape Leeuwin in Western Australia,

417
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:35,040
‎繼續行至塔斯馬尼亞島的東南角
then down around the South East Cape in Tasmania,

418
00:31:35,120 --> 00:31:36,910
‎最后回到悉尼港
and back up to Sydney Harbor.

419
00:31:37,950 --> 00:31:39,290
‎所以 其實不算太難啦
So not so much really.

420
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:44,040
‎跟我來
Come on!

421
00:31:44,120 --> 00:31:47,830
‎好了 這是開船用的舵柄
All right, so this is the tiller to steer,

422
00:31:47,910 --> 00:31:50,040
‎但目前處于自動駕駛模式
but it's on autopilot at the moment.

423
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:52,160
‎這下面是救生艇
Uh, the lifeboat is under here,

424
00:31:52,250 --> 00:31:54,450
‎這里面是浮錨
and in here is the drogue.

425
00:31:54,950 --> 00:31:56,950
‎它類似于船錨 不過是軟的
It's like a soft anchor.

426
00:31:57,040 --> 00:32:00,500
‎它能讓船在風暴中減速和保持穩定
It slows the boat down during storms and keeps it stable.

427
00:32:02,250 --> 00:32:04,000
‎這是我的淋浴用品
Here's my shower,

428
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:07,870
‎但我好像把梳子落家里了
although I have discovered that I left my hairbrush at home.

429
00:32:07,950 --> 00:32:11,120
‎所以接下來的200天 只好用這個代替
So I'll just have to use this for 200 days.

430
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,410
‎至少后院的景致值回票價了
At least the backyard makes up for it, though.

431
00:32:33,290 --> 00:32:34,500
‎餓了嗎 科比
Hungry, Kobi?

432
00:32:45,450 --> 00:32:46,910
‎-杰絲 ‎-嘿
-Jess. -Hey.

433
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:52,000
‎船舶偵測警報運作正常 ‎有一艘船剛從我的西北邊駛過
Uh, ship detection alarms work. Uh, one just went past northwest of me.

434
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:56,370
‎好的 在這之后的很長一段時間 ‎你都不會再看到其他船只
Good to know. Well, that'll be the last ship you see for a while now.

435
00:32:57,370 --> 00:32:58,330
‎你怎么知道
How do you know?

436
00:33:01,370 --> 00:33:05,080
‎聽著 你要從那次撞船中 ‎吸取教訓 好嗎
Listen, let that crash be a lesson to you, eh?

437
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:08,410
‎你現在知道該怎么處理了
You know how to handle it now.

438
00:33:12,250 --> 00:33:14,910
‎-你會覺得孤單嗎  ‎-有時候會
-Did you ever get lonely? -Oh, sometimes.

439
00:33:15,870 --> 00:33:18,790
‎-但我知道該怎么克服 ‎-怎么克服
-But I know how to get over it. -How?

440
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:20,540
‎唱歌
-Sing.

441
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:23,080
‎唱歌 你會唱歌
-Sing? You-- You sang?

442
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:25,450
‎我們是水手 當然要唱歌
We're sailors. That's what we're supposed to do.

443
00:33:27,870 --> 00:33:29,410
‎去睡會兒吧 好嗎
Try to get some sleep, eh?

444
00:33:30,330 --> 00:33:33,540
‎你只是在航程第一周有點緊張罷了 ‎喔 有魚上鉤了
You've just got the first-week jitters, that's all. Oh! Fish are calling.

445
00:33:33,620 --> 00:33:34,580
‎-我得先掛了 ‎-好
-Gotta go. -Okay.

446
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:37,620
‎來吧
Come on.

447
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,120
‎可惡
Oh, bugger!

448
00:33:45,910 --> 00:33:49,750
‎（第12天 太平洋水域 臨近斐濟）

449
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:21,500
‎…本地女孩引起全國關注
…the local girl who is now attracting national attention.

450
00:34:21,580 --> 00:34:26,500
‎杰西卡沃森一家 ‎曾駕駛特制的雙層巴士周游澳洲
Jessica Watson's family traveled Australia in a purpose-built double-decker bus

451
00:34:26,580 --> 00:34:30,250
‎后來在杰西卡九歲時 ‎搬到了船上居住
before moving onto a boat when Jessica was nine.

452
00:34:30,330 --> 00:34:35,540
‎如今 七年后 杰西卡即將跨越 ‎人生中的第一個重要里程碑
the first major milestone in her attempt to be the youngest person… Now, seven years later, Jessica is about to cross

453
00:34:35,620 --> 00:34:40,000
‎挑戰單人環球航海 ‎成為完成此舉的最年輕人士
…to sail solo around the world. There we go.

454
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:44,160
‎謝謝你 蘇西 ‎真正的危險在印度洋和南冰洋海域
Thanks, Susie. The real danger, of course, will be the Indian and Southern Oceans, where dozens of sailors,

455
00:34:44,250 --> 00:34:48,200
‎在那里 數十位比杰西卡沃森 ‎更為經驗豐富的水手
who are far more experienced than young Jessica Watson,

456
00:34:48,290 --> 00:34:50,620
‎都曾接二連三地經歷了翻船
have endured knockdown after knockdown.

457
00:34:50,700 --> 00:34:52,000
‎沒必要給我們聽這個
Didn't need to hear that.

458
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:56,200
‎嘗試環球航行的獨自航海人 ‎要忍受數月的…
-Solo sailors looking to circumnavigate the globe endure many months…

459
00:34:57,790 --> 00:35:01,870
‎穿越赤道對水手來說是一件大事
Okay, so crossing the equator is a big deal for sailors.

460
00:35:01,950 --> 00:35:03,500
‎你由此證明自己的航海實力
You've proven your seaworthiness and must be initiated

461
00:35:03,580 --> 00:35:06,040
‎被正式接納為水手團體的一員
into the Fraternity of Mariners.

462
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:08,250
‎好的 那么…
Okay, so…

463
00:35:08,330 --> 00:35:14,250
‎赤道以南 20米 15米 ‎十 五 零
South, twenty, fifteen, ten, five, zero!

464
00:35:14,330 --> 00:35:17,700
‎我們從南半球進入北半球啦
We crossed from the Southern Hemisphere into the Northern Hemisphere!

465
00:35:18,750 --> 00:35:20,750
‎好的 作為我的入團儀式…
Okay, for the initiation ceremony…

466
00:35:31,700 --> 00:35:33,410
‎好清爽啊
Quite refreshing, actually.

467
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:35,660
‎敬海神
A toast to King Neptune!

468
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:42,160
‎（第33天 赤道 離家7010公里）

469
00:35:42,250 --> 00:35:45,040
‎-敬杰西 ‎-杰西 干杯
-To Jess. -To Jess! Cheers!

470
00:35:48,290 --> 00:35:51,830
‎真不敢相信 ‎她已經穿越了赤道 太酷了
I can't believe she's crossed the equator. So cool.

471
00:35:54,580 --> 00:35:58,870
‎（澳洲 ‎北美洲-南美洲）

472
00:36:02,830 --> 00:36:07,370
‎紅色晚霞 水手歡喜 ‎紅色朝霞 水手警醒
Red sky at night, sailor's delight. Red sky in the morning, sailor's warning.

473
00:36:16,580 --> 00:36:17,830
‎看天氣預報了嗎
See the forecast?

474
00:36:17,910 --> 00:36:19,410
‎嗯 天象已經說明了一切
Yeah, sky says it all.

475
00:36:20,790 --> 00:36:24,910
‎對 杰絲 這會是一場大風暴 ‎我們來商量對策吧
Yeah. Jess, this is gonna be a big one. Let's talk game, eh?

476
00:36:26,660 --> 00:36:28,080
‎我會改變航向
I'll change course.

477
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:32,370
‎我的建議是拋出浮錨 抗過去
I think you should launch the drogue. Weather it.

478
00:36:34,580 --> 00:36:35,870
‎穿過風暴
Go through the storm?

479
00:36:35,950 --> 00:36:39,290
‎風暴的移動速度很快 ‎你不可能繞過去的
Well, it's moving fast. There's no way you're gonna outrun it.

480
00:36:39,950 --> 00:36:42,500
‎-但只要抗住 它很快就過去了 ‎-謝天謝地
But that also means it's gonna pass quickly. -Thank God.

481
00:36:42,580 --> 00:36:45,660
‎慢著 我們說好了安全至上的
-W-- Hang on, hang on. We agreed to do whatever's safest.

482
00:36:45,750 --> 00:36:48,750
‎風暴在這個區域并不常見 ‎爸爸 很難判斷的
Storms in this region aren't common, Dad. It's hard to judge.

483
00:36:50,370 --> 00:36:51,620
‎浮錨就像船錨一樣
It's like an anchor.

484
00:36:51,700 --> 00:36:54,830
‎會幫助她保持穩定 她不會有事的
The drogue will keep her stable. She'll be okay.

485
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:59,830
‎我認為這是最好的選擇 ‎杰絲 你決定吧
I think it's our best option, Jess. It's your call.

486
00:37:04,830 --> 00:37:05,660
‎好吧
Okay.

487
00:37:08,830 --> 00:37:10,160
‎跟我說說
-Talk to me.

488
00:37:10,250 --> 00:37:12,580
‎操作流程 對 我們分解研究一下
Protocols. Yeah, let's break it down.

489
00:37:12,660 --> 00:37:15,870
‎我不知道 我不喜歡這計劃
I don't know. I don't-- I don't like this.

490
00:37:15,950 --> 00:37:19,660
‎不管你怎么想 本是專業的 杰絲也是
Ben knows his stuff, whatever you think of him. What's more, so does Jess.

491
00:37:22,910 --> 00:37:24,330
‎你知道該怎么做
-You know the drill.

492
00:37:24,410 --> 00:37:25,290
‎對
-Yeah.

493
00:39:59,830 --> 00:40:00,910
‎來吧 浮錨
Come on, drogue!

494
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:17,950
‎我有話跟你們說 ‎我想獨自駕船環球航行
I have something to tell you. I want to circumnavigate the world solo.

495
00:41:18,040 --> 00:41:21,120
‎并打破達成這一成就的最小年齡紀錄
And I'm gonna be the youngest person to do it.

496
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:23,080
杰絲…
Uh, Jess…

497
00:41:23,580 --> 00:41:24,500
‎什么
What?

498
00:41:25,450 --> 00:41:29,410
‎杰西馬丁17歲就做到了 ‎他是個跟我一樣的普通小孩
Jesse Martin did it when he was 17. He was an ordinary kid, so am I.

499
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:33,660
‎我已經計劃好了
Don't worry, I've got a plan.

500
00:41:33,750 --> 00:41:36,450
‎我要找個老師 拿到資格證
I'll get a teacher, qualifications.

501
00:41:36,540 --> 00:41:41,370
‎這上面列出了所有我需要做的事 ‎還有一開始要上的安全課
Here's a list of all the things I'll need and the safety courses I'll do to start.

502
00:41:43,540 --> 00:41:47,830
‎我會通過打工掙錢和拉贊助 ‎來支付重大開銷
I'll get jobs to earn money, and find sponsors to cover the big costs,

503
00:41:47,910 --> 00:41:52,200
‎每航海一個小時 ‎我都會相應地做一小時閱讀
and for every hour I sail, I'll still do an hour of reading.

504
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,700
‎那閱讀量可不小呢
-Now, that's a good amount of reading!

505
00:41:54,790 --> 00:41:56,580
‎-她很了解自己的聽眾 ‎-是啊
-She knows her audience. -Yeah.

506
00:41:56,660 --> 00:42:00,250
‎那你就開始實施這些計劃吧
Well, uh, you'd better start working through that list, then. Thoroughly.

507
00:42:00,830 --> 00:42:03,660
‎只要你下定決心的事 一定能辦到
I think you can do anything you set your mind to, honey.

508
00:42:23,620 --> 00:42:25,830
‎杰絲 你沒事吧
-Jess! You okay?

509
00:42:26,830 --> 00:42:29,540
‎-我沒事 ‎-出什么事了 你怎么沒來電話
-Yeah, I'm fine. -What happened? Why didn't you call?

510
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:33,700
‎我被東西砸暈了 但我沒事
Well, I got knocked out, but I'm fine.

511
00:42:33,790 --> 00:42:36,370
‎-什么  ‎-砸暈了 你還好嗎
-What? -Knocked out? Are you okay?

512
00:42:36,450 --> 00:42:38,370
‎-有腦震蕩嗎  ‎-帥啊
-Do you have a concussion? -Sick.

513
00:42:38,450 --> 00:42:41,620
‎-你需要醫生  ‎-船上沒有
-You need a doctor! -Oh, I didn't pack one of those.

514
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:43,330
‎杰絲 聽完說
Hey, come on. Jess, listen to me.

515
00:42:43,410 --> 00:42:46,660
‎你覺得頭痛 耳鳴 惡心嗎
Do you have a headache, ringing in the ears, or nausea or something?

516
00:42:46,750 --> 00:42:48,700
‎爸爸 別大驚小怪了 我沒事
Dad, please stop. I'm fine.

517
00:42:50,540 --> 00:42:51,500
‎本在嗎
Is Ben there?

518
00:42:55,250 --> 00:42:56,250
‎小粉怎么樣
How's Pink?

519
00:42:59,790 --> 00:43:01,160
‎它沒事
Yeah, she's all right.

520
00:43:01,250 --> 00:43:02,790
‎你沒系好安全帶嗎
You weren't strapped in, were you?

521
00:43:03,370 --> 00:43:06,750
‎-我當時正準備系呢 ‎-你應該更早系好
-I was getting there. -Well, you should've already been there.

522
00:43:07,330 --> 00:43:10,410
‎大自然從來不等人 你知道的
Mother Nature doesn't wait for anyone. You know that, Jess.

523
00:43:10,500 --> 00:43:12,750
‎-那可是風暴啊 ‎-不管是什么
It was a storm. It doesn't matter.

524
00:43:12,830 --> 00:43:16,330
‎你都得處理好 ‎這次能平安度過是你運氣好
You have to manage it. You're just lucky you got through this one.

525
00:43:16,910 --> 00:43:19,830
‎真是太瘋狂了 ‎我原本還打算繞過去的
It was so wild, Ben. I thought we were gonna go all the way around.

526
00:43:19,910 --> 00:43:21,410
‎是啊
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

527
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:33,040
‎（第50天 南美洲近海岸）

528
00:43:44,870 --> 00:43:46,250
‎本出來了 快來
Oh, it's Ben. Let's go.

529
00:43:46,330 --> 00:43:50,410
‎我們聽說杰絲經歷了第一場風暴 ‎有任何損傷嗎
Ben! We just had word Jess went through her first storm. Any injuries or damage?

530
00:43:50,500 --> 00:43:54,450
‎我們不會回答任何問題 ‎但杰絲建了一個博客 這是地址
We aren't taking any questions, but Jess has a blog at this address.

531
00:43:55,870 --> 00:43:57,290
‎轉移視線的基本法
Diversion 101.

532
00:43:59,080 --> 00:44:00,660
‎其實也沒那么難呀 本
It's not that hard, Ben.

533
00:44:00,750 --> 00:44:04,870
‎-本 你有什么要補充的嗎  ‎-本 不好意思 就一會兒
Is there anything you can add? Ben, excuse me. Excuse me! Just one sec. She's going through--

534
00:44:05,540 --> 00:44:08,040
‎-等一下 本 抱歉 ‎-吉米 幫我拿一下
-Wait! Wait, Ben, sorry. -Jimmy, hold this.

535
00:44:14,080 --> 00:44:17,870
‎在大海中央航行 ‎信天翁是唯一可見的生物
An albatross, one of the only living things you see in the middle of the ocean.

536
00:44:17,950 --> 00:44:20,450
‎它們一直以來都是水手們觀察的目標
They've been watched by sailors throughout history.

537
00:44:20,540 --> 00:44:21,950
‎我好像釣到魚啦
I think I caught a fish!

538
00:44:25,540 --> 00:44:26,370
‎好的
Okay.

539
00:44:37,080 --> 00:44:37,950
‎好嘞
Ooh! Okay.

540
00:44:41,870 --> 00:44:45,000
‎過來 能看見嗎
Come over here! Can you see it?

541
00:44:47,500 --> 00:44:48,500
‎你好呀
Oh! Hello.

542
00:44:49,790 --> 00:44:50,660
‎該我了
-My turn!

543
00:44:51,580 --> 00:44:53,580
‎好了 湯姆 早餐好了
All right! Tom, grub's up!

544
00:44:54,870 --> 00:44:55,950
‎-好的 ‎-來了
-Yup. -Here you go.

545
00:44:57,290 --> 00:44:58,290
‎吃吧
-Eat up! -Thank you.

546
00:45:01,040 --> 00:45:01,870
‎早上好
Morning!

547
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:06,330
‎本 這是你的
Ben? Here you go.

548
00:45:06,830 --> 00:45:08,450
‎我不吃早餐
I don't eat breakfast.

549
00:45:09,370 --> 00:45:12,080
‎不吃就不吃吧 ‎但你想吃的話 隨時可以
Uh, well, don't then, but it's here if you want it.

550
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:13,580
‎想寫點什么嗎
Want to write something?

551
00:45:17,250 --> 00:45:18,950
‎（湯姆國王）

552
00:45:41,790 --> 00:45:43,830
‎杰絲 我被悉尼大學錄取啦
Jess, I got into Sydney Uni!

553
00:45:44,580 --> 00:45:48,950
‎天吶 艾米莉 太棒了  ‎恭喜呀 你成功啦
Oh, my gosh! Em, that's fantastic! Congratulations, you did it!

554
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:51,200
‎漢娜已經在預謀霸占我的床了
I should warn you, Hannah's already gunning for my bed.

555
00:45:51,290 --> 00:45:52,580
‎對哦
Right.

556
00:45:53,200 --> 00:45:55,160
‎等我回去你都走了
Oh, you'll be gone before I get back.

557
00:45:56,000 --> 00:45:57,910
‎但我還是會幫你打理博客的
Yeah, I'll still run the blog, though.

558
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:01,250
‎我在游泳嘉年華上贏了四枚獎牌哦
Jess, I won four medals at the swimming carnival!

559
00:46:01,330 --> 00:46:05,500
‎漢娜 太棒啦 真希望我能親眼看到
Wow, Han! That's amazing! I wish I could have been there.

560
00:46:05,580 --> 00:46:07,660
‎知道嗎 湯姆交女朋友了
And guess what? Tom has a date.

561
00:46:08,500 --> 00:46:11,080
‎-你干嗎… ‎-什么 誰呀
-Why would you-- -What? With who?

562
00:46:11,160 --> 00:46:12,830
‎給我…
-Give me the… Okay.

563
00:46:12,910 --> 00:46:14,080
‎杰絲
-Jess! -I want the phone!

564
00:46:14,160 --> 00:46:17,790
‎-我沒有 我不知道她在說什么… ‎-他有
I don't, I don't! -I don't know what-- -Yes, he does!

565
00:46:17,870 --> 00:46:20,250
‎他有
-I'm telling her! -He does! He does!

566
00:46:20,330 --> 00:46:23,040
‎讓我跟她說 我來告訴她是誰
I'm talking to her and I'm telling her who it is!

567
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:24,330
‎我沒有女朋友
I don't have-- I don't have a date.

568
00:46:24,410 --> 00:46:26,200
‎-他有  ‎-我沒有女朋友
-He does! -I don't have a date.

569
00:46:36,620 --> 00:46:37,500
‎我贏了
Snap.

570
00:46:43,700 --> 00:46:46,410
‎-繼續 你收到了什么  ‎-沖浪板
-Go on, what do you got? -Boogie board!

571
00:46:46,500 --> 00:46:47,790
‎什么 沖浪板
-What? A boogie board?

572
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:51,330
‎漢娜吃糖吃瘋了
You'll be shocked to hear that Hannah's riled up on sugar.

573
00:46:54,500 --> 00:46:58,290
‎我也是 這都還沒到圣誕節呢
Well, she's not the only one. And it's not even Christmas here yet.

574
00:46:58,870 --> 00:47:01,000
‎-艾米莉在嗎  ‎-在 等一下
-Oh, is Em around? -Yeah, hold on!

575
00:47:02,040 --> 00:47:03,080
‎艾米莉
Em.

576
00:47:05,200 --> 00:47:07,000
‎嘿 杰絲 圣誕快樂
Hey, Jess. Merry Christmas!

577
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:08,750
‎圣誕快樂
Merry Christmas!

578
00:47:10,080 --> 00:47:12,040
‎一包友情種子
A Grow Your Own Friend!

579
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:14,200
‎謝謝 太合我心意啦
Aw, thank you, Em, it's just what I need.

580
00:47:15,580 --> 00:47:17,450
‎我聽說植物是很棒的傾聽者
-Yeah, I hear she's a great listener.

581
00:47:18,120 --> 00:47:19,410
‎-該我了  ‎-爸要跟你說
-Hey, my turn! -Oh, here's Dad.

582
00:47:20,790 --> 00:47:23,910
‎圣誕快樂 親愛的 聽說你有新朋友了
Merry Christmas, love. Hey, I hear you've got a new mate.

583
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:26,250
‎你們明天有什么安排
What have you two got planned for tomorrow then?

584
00:47:26,330 --> 00:47:29,830
‎我會主辦派對 ‎但我的客人們要比你那邊安靜多了
Oh, well, I'm hosting, uh, but my guests are a little quieter than yours.

585
00:47:30,450 --> 00:47:31,870
‎好酷呀 漢娜
-That's pretty cool, Hannah.

586
00:47:31,950 --> 00:47:34,450
‎聽起來真不錯 我能到你那邊去嗎
That sounds great! Mind if I come to yours?

587
00:47:35,870 --> 00:47:38,700
‎杰絲 我忘說了 去找裝大蔥的袋子
Jess! I forgot. Find the leeks bag.

588
00:47:38,790 --> 00:47:40,660
‎你聽見了嗎 裝大蔥的袋子
Do you hear that? Leeks bag.

589
00:47:50,910 --> 00:47:51,790
‎本
Ben!

590
00:47:53,080 --> 00:47:55,540
‎-圣誕快樂  ‎-對
Merry Christmas! Yeah.

591
00:47:56,830 --> 00:47:57,910
‎進來吧
Come on in.

592
00:47:58,000 --> 00:47:59,580
‎圣誕快樂 本
Merry Christmas, Ben!

593
00:48:00,500 --> 00:48:03,000
‎-圣誕快樂 本  ‎-好
-Merry Christmas, Ben! -Yeah.

594
00:48:04,200 --> 00:48:05,750
‎圣誕快樂 伙計
Merry Christmas, mate.

595
00:48:07,200 --> 00:48:08,410
‎-給 ‎-謝謝
-There you are. -Oh, thanks.

596
00:48:12,450 --> 00:48:14,870
‎我很喜歡 謝啦 湯姆
Oh, I love them. Thank you, Tom.

597
00:48:19,330 --> 00:48:22,830
‎好了 你們那邊有點吵 我先掛了哦
All right, it's a bit loud. I'm gonna go now.

598
00:48:23,830 --> 00:48:25,330
‎大家說再見
Everybody say goodbye to Jess!

599
00:48:25,410 --> 00:48:27,700
‎-我們愛你  ‎-好的 回聊 杰絲
-We love you! -Yeah, see you, Jess!

600
00:48:27,790 --> 00:48:29,080
‎湯姆 音樂
Tom, music!

601
00:48:29,660 --> 00:48:30,500
‎好
Yup.

602
00:48:32,620 --> 00:48:34,580
‎-拿著 ‎-好啊 干杯
-Take this. -Yeah. Cheers.

603
00:48:35,660 --> 00:48:36,950
‎是啊 你就像…
Yeah, you're like…

604
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:42,370
‎好了 飯菜上桌嘍 來吃吧
All right, food's on the table! Come on, you lot.

605
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:55,250
‎大伙兒都餓了吧
Hope you're hungry!

606
00:48:55,330 --> 00:48:58,040
‎好了 拉炮時間 漢娜 來 用力拉
Right, cracker time, Han, come on. Big pull!

607
00:49:00,290 --> 00:49:01,290
‎抱歉 本
-Sorry, Ben. -Ben.

608
00:49:07,080 --> 00:49:09,620
‎本 你往常都怎么過圣誕節呀
Ben, what do you usually do for Christmas?

609
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:11,830
‎不過
Nothing.

610
00:49:13,290 --> 00:49:14,870
‎你的家人呢
What about your family?

611
00:49:16,910 --> 00:49:18,080
‎沒有家人
Oh. Uh, don't have one.

612
00:49:38,950 --> 00:49:40,830
‎-圣誕快樂 ‎-給我的
-Merry Christmas. -For me?

613
00:49:41,660 --> 00:49:42,870
‎打開看看
Open it, open it!

614
00:49:51,870 --> 00:49:52,870
‎謝謝
Thank you.

615
00:49:54,790 --> 00:49:57,700
‎本 為什么合恩角那么重要
Ben, why is Cape Horn such a big deal?

616
00:49:58,200 --> 00:49:59,040
‎這個嘛…
Oh! Well…

617
00:49:59,870 --> 00:50:02,160
‎它可是非常考驗航海技術的
That is some wicked sailing.

618
00:50:02,250 --> 00:50:06,160
‎那里是大西洋和太平洋的交匯處
See, that's where the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans meet,

619
00:50:06,250 --> 00:50:11,450
‎有狂風呼嘯 洋流翻騰
so you get these powerful winds, these churning currents,

620
00:50:11,540 --> 00:50:15,830
‎還有兩大洋相互碰撞時 ‎掀起的滔天的巨浪
these humongous waves as the oceans smash together.

621
00:50:17,450 --> 00:50:21,000
‎正因如此 那段航道兇險萬分
That's why that passage is so sinister.

622
00:50:22,080 --> 00:50:27,370
‎海里飄滿了前輩水手們的…手指尖
It's absolutely littered with a long-lost trail of fingertips.

623
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:36,040
‎本 你在說到我們女兒身處險境時 ‎能別這么興奮嗎
-Uh, Ben? Uh, could you maybe be a little less excited about our daughter doing something sinister?

624
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:36,950
‎好吧
All right.

625
00:50:38,250 --> 00:50:40,370
‎你是指船會開得很快嗎
We talking fast sailing?

626
00:50:42,870 --> 00:50:43,870
‎快得不得了
-Wicked fast.

627
00:50:44,910 --> 00:50:46,080
‎天啊
-Oh, my.

628
00:50:46,160 --> 00:50:51,200
‎（第82天 合恩角 離家17420公里）

629
00:51:06,540 --> 00:51:09,160
‎瞧她現在船速多快啊 天吶
Look how fast she's going. Bloody hell.

630
00:51:11,540 --> 00:51:14,200
-別開太快呀 ‎-她開得好快
Oh, not-- not too fast. It's… -She's going quick.

631
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:18,000
‎加油啊
Come on!

632
00:51:18,500 --> 00:51:21,500
‎我們剛剛繞過了 ‎航海界的珠峰 合恩角
We just rounded the Everest of the ocean, Cape Horn,

633
00:51:21,580 --> 00:51:24,250
‎我很高興地宣布 這次航行很順利
and I am happy to report it was smooth sailing.

634
00:51:24,950 --> 00:51:26,160
‎而且很酷
And so cool!

635
00:51:26,950 --> 00:51:28,370
‎我真不敢相信
I, uh-- I just-- I just can't believe it.

636
00:51:28,450 --> 00:51:30,540
‎我們通過了最大的挑戰
It's like we've passed our biggest challenge.

637
00:51:30,620 --> 00:51:35,540
‎（南美洲-非洲）

638
00:51:35,620 --> 00:51:41,870
‎（第113天 沒有風的第一天 ‎離家20735公里）

639
00:51:46,910 --> 00:51:47,950
‎你聽見了嗎
Do you hear that?

640
00:51:49,500 --> 00:51:51,120
‎一點聲音也沒有
It's the sound of nothing.

641
00:51:52,450 --> 00:51:53,870
‎萬籟俱寂
Nothing at all.

642
00:51:56,370 --> 00:51:59,040
‎沒有風 沒有海浪
There's no wind or waves.

643
00:51:59,750 --> 00:52:01,120
‎已經好幾天了
It's been days.

644
00:52:10,250 --> 00:52:11,540
‎你知道我在哪里
You know where I am.

645
00:52:23,540 --> 00:52:27,200
‎我要環球航海 ‎現在聘請你當我的教練
I'm gonna sail around the world and I'm hiring you as my coach.

646
00:52:27,700 --> 00:52:30,750
‎告訴你爸媽 航海學校有一大堆教練
Tell your parents there's plenty of coaches at the sailing school.

647
00:52:30,830 --> 00:52:33,660
‎-我知道 但我想跟你學 ‎-可是…
Well… I know, but I want you to do it.

648
00:52:35,950 --> 00:52:37,540
‎我已經不再航海了
I don't sail anymore.

649
00:52:37,620 --> 00:52:39,950
‎因為千禧杯的事 我知道
Because of the Millennium Cup, I know.

650
00:52:42,500 --> 00:52:45,540
‎但如果你的學生 ‎成為了歷史上最年輕的
But if you help the youngest person in history

651
00:52:45,620 --> 00:52:47,700
‎獨自完成環球航海的人
sail solo around the world,

652
00:52:47,790 --> 00:52:50,750
‎人們就不會揪著馬特特納的事不放了
people will let go of what happened with Matt Turner.

653
00:52:50,830 --> 00:52:52,790
‎他們也許會放下 但我不會
They might, but I won't.

654
00:52:56,290 --> 00:52:58,330
‎話說回來 你為什么想干這個
Hey, why-- why do you want to do this, anyway?

655
00:53:00,410 --> 00:53:03,200
‎因為這年頭沒有人再去探險了
‎'Cause… no one explores anymore.

656
00:53:03,950 --> 00:53:08,080
‎登上太空的人比環球航海的人還多
You know, there have been more people in space than have sailed around the world.

657
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:12,830
‎我之前甚至不知道有環球航海這回事 ‎但它確實存在 而我想去做
I didn't even know it was something you can do, but you can, and I want to.

658
00:53:13,750 --> 00:53:16,290
‎因為我是個探險家
'Cause I'm an adventurer.

659
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:19,410
‎你喜歡航海
You like sailing.

660
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:23,410
‎但環球航行完全是另一回事
Circumnavigating the globe is a whole different thing, mate.

661
00:53:23,500 --> 00:53:26,200
‎我想自己去尋找答案
Well, that's what I want to find out for myself.

662
00:53:29,620 --> 00:53:32,160
‎無論我說什么 ‎都無法動搖你的決心 對嗎
You're gonna do this no matter what I say, aren't you?

663
00:53:34,330 --> 00:53:38,200
‎如果我答應了 ‎我可是不會給你特別待遇的
If I was going to agree to this, I'm not gonna treat you special,

664
00:53:38,870 --> 00:53:40,950
‎因為大海對所有人一視同仁
'cause it doesn't matter out there.

665
00:53:41,040 --> 00:53:43,700
‎我只會像對待自己一樣嚴格要求你
I'll only treat you how I treat myself.

666
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:49,910
第一條規則 別抱我
First rule… don't do that.

667
00:53:51,000 --> 00:53:52,120
‎嚇死我了
It freaks me out.

668
00:53:52,200 --> 00:53:58,830
‎（第115天 無風的第三天）

669
00:54:07,950 --> 00:54:10,370
‎（保持堅強 爸爸）

670
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:19,200
‎-就是這樣 來吧 ‎-好
-That's it. Come on. -Okay.

671
00:54:20,700 --> 00:54:23,660
‎本 你都好幾天沒睡了 休息一下吧
-Ben, you've barely slept in days, mate. -Take a break.

672
00:54:23,750 --> 00:54:25,580
‎什么 不用 我沒事
-Oh, nah. No, no. I'm good.

673
00:54:26,540 --> 00:54:29,000
‎只是在等日志更新
Just, um, waiting on these logs.

674
00:54:29,950 --> 00:54:31,910
‎杰絲在干什么
What is Jess doing?

675
00:54:38,950 --> 00:54:44,370
‎（第117天 無風的第五天）

676
00:55:17,080 --> 00:55:18,080
‎杰絲
Jess?

677
00:55:18,870 --> 00:55:21,120
‎你已經反方向行駛幾個小時了
You've been going backwards for hours, mate.

678
00:55:21,200 --> 00:55:22,620
‎對 我之前睡著了
Yeah, I was asleep.

679
00:55:23,750 --> 00:55:25,950
‎你沒設置警報嗎
So you didn't set the alarms?

680
00:55:26,830 --> 00:55:29,450
‎一周都沒怎么挪動 ‎我怎么知道船會倒著走
Well, barely moved in a week, how would I know we're going backwards?

681
00:55:29,540 --> 00:55:32,000
‎所以才要設置警報啊
Again, that's why you set the alarms, mate!

682
00:55:32,080 --> 00:55:33,620
‎對 好吧 冷靜點
Yeah, okay, chill out.

683
00:55:33,700 --> 00:55:37,040
‎“冷靜” 這樣很危險 好吧
"Chill out"? Hey, this is dangerous, okay?

684
00:55:37,660 --> 00:55:39,750
‎就是這種時候會出差錯 會有人受傷
This is when things go wrong, when people get hurt,

685
00:55:39,830 --> 00:55:42,000
‎因為某些人的玩忽職守
when people neglect their responsibilities!

686
00:55:42,080 --> 00:55:45,500
‎再這樣下去 你會害死自己的
And you, if you keep on like this, you're gonna get yourself killed!

687
00:55:46,500 --> 00:55:47,910
‎是嗎 這種事你最清楚了
Yeah? Well, you'd know!

688
00:55:49,750 --> 00:55:50,950
‎喂 什么情況
Oi! What's going on?

689
00:55:52,290 --> 00:55:53,370
‎我…
I, uh…

690
00:55:56,540 --> 00:55:57,660
‎你說得對 杰絲
You're right, Jess.

691
00:55:58,290 --> 00:55:59,160
‎對
Yeah.

692
00:56:00,000 --> 00:56:01,200
‎我需要冷靜一下
I need to chill out.

693
00:56:08,790 --> 00:56:09,620
‎杰絲
Jess?

694
00:56:18,870 --> 00:56:22,080
‎這里沒有風 沒有浪
There's no wind, and there's no waves,

695
00:56:22,160 --> 00:56:24,330
‎現在連本也不理我了
and now there's no Ben.

696
00:56:25,790 --> 00:56:28,330
‎只剩我一個人
And it's just me.

697
00:56:30,290 --> 00:56:34,120
‎而我無法擺脫我自己
And I-- I can't get away from myself.

698
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:51,830
‎（第119天 無風的第七天）

699
00:56:51,910 --> 00:56:53,250
‎我還是停在原地
I still haven't moved.

700
00:56:54,620 --> 00:56:58,120
‎謝天謝地 你終于接電話了  ‎出什么事了 杰絲
Oh, thank God you picked up! What's going on, Jess?

701
00:56:59,620 --> 00:57:00,450
‎媽媽
Mum.

702
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:03,870
‎怎么啦
What is it?

703
00:57:09,040 --> 00:57:10,700
‎沒事了 我在呢
It's okay. I'm here.

704
00:57:12,410 --> 00:57:13,410
‎說吧
Get it out.

705
00:57:17,750 --> 00:57:19,160
‎我太孤單了
I'm so alone.

706
00:57:22,370 --> 00:57:23,290
‎不 你不是一個人
No, you're not.

707
00:57:26,160 --> 00:57:29,750
‎我知道孤單的感覺有多可怕
I know how awful it is to feel like this.

708
00:57:30,410 --> 00:57:33,500
‎但不會一直這樣下去的
But… it won't last forever.

709
00:57:35,870 --> 00:57:38,500
‎我沒法告訴你何時會起風
I can't tell you when the wind will pick up,

710
00:57:39,330 --> 00:57:41,410
但我知道只要你堅持下去
‎but… I know that if you keep going,

711
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:43,250
‎風一定會來的
it will.

712
00:57:45,950 --> 00:57:47,370
‎就像你的每一位
Just as it has done

713
00:57:47,870 --> 00:57:50,580
‎水手前輩都經歷過的那樣
for every sailor before you.

714
00:57:57,160 --> 00:58:00,000
‎還記得我以前常給你唱的那首歌嗎
Do you remember the song I used to sing to you at night?

715
00:58:00,580 --> 00:58:01,410
‎嗯
Yeah.

716
00:58:03,290 --> 00:58:06,700
‎我要你去找夜空中最明亮的那顆星
I want you to search for the brightest star in the sky.

717
00:58:08,790 --> 00:58:10,620
‎每當你凝望它的時候
And every time you look at it,

718
00:58:11,410 --> 00:58:14,370
‎要知道遠在家中的我…
at home… know that I'm here,

719
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:19,330
‎也凝望著同一顆星辰
staring at that same star.

720
00:58:23,790 --> 00:58:24,790
‎我與你同在
I'm with you.

721
00:58:28,080 --> 00:58:28,910
‎知道嗎
Okay?

722
00:58:30,040 --> 00:58:30,870
‎嗯 好
Yeah, okay.

723
00:58:37,580 --> 00:58:38,700
‎我愛你 杰絲
I love you, Jess.

724
00:58:38,790 --> 00:58:40,250
‎我也愛你
I love you too.

725
00:58:55,040 --> 00:59:00,160
‎有一個外星人在天上等待

726
00:59:00,790 --> 00:59:02,790
‎他想過來見我們

727
00:59:02,870 --> 00:59:05,250
‎但害怕嚇到我們

728
00:59:05,330 --> 00:59:10,160
‎有一個外星人在天上等待

729
00:59:45,660 --> 00:59:46,660
‎嗨
Hi.

730
00:59:48,580 --> 00:59:50,410
‎抱歉 我最近沒怎么錄視頻
Sorry I haven't been here much.

731
00:59:52,410 --> 00:59:55,040
‎我在逃避
I've been avoiding a lot.

732
00:59:59,500 --> 01:00:03,160
‎老實說 實現夢想的過程很艱難
Mmm, the truth is that living your dream is hard.

733
01:00:04,410 --> 01:00:06,700
‎而現在異常艱辛
And right now it's really hard.

734
01:00:08,410 --> 01:00:10,410
‎我哭了好幾個小時
I've been crying for hours.

735
01:00:11,410 --> 01:00:12,660
‎我很疲憊
I'm tired.

736
01:00:13,950 --> 01:00:15,040
‎我全身酸痛
I'm sore.

737
01:00:16,000 --> 01:00:19,200
‎連腿都伸展不開
I can't properly stretch my legs.

738
01:00:22,040 --> 01:00:23,870
‎我想念我的家人
I miss my family.

739
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:29,330
‎很想很想
I miss them a lot.

740
01:00:32,250 --> 01:00:34,750
‎我也想我那個愛發脾氣的顧問…
And I miss my grouchy advisor…

741
01:00:37,160 --> 01:00:39,000
‎他也是我最好的朋友
…who's also my best friend.

742
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:46,290
‎一直以來
Ah, but through it all,

743
01:00:46,370 --> 01:00:50,450
‎我都在努力做一個堅韌不拔的探險家
I've tried to be this-- this tough, stoic explorer.

744
01:00:50,540 --> 01:00:54,910
‎但那不是真的我 知道嗎
And… that's not me, you know?

745
01:00:57,000 --> 01:01:01,790
‎我并不總是樂觀向上 ‎內心強大 無所畏懼的
I'm not always fine, or strong, or fearless.

746
01:01:03,200 --> 01:01:06,200
‎無所畏懼…我經常會害怕
Phew! "Fearless." I'm often terrified!

747
01:01:07,200 --> 01:01:09,000
‎會懷疑自己
And I doubt myself.

748
01:01:10,040 --> 01:01:11,040
‎而且…
And…

749
01:01:13,200 --> 01:01:15,000
‎經常會想要放棄
I think a lot about giving up.

750
01:01:20,250 --> 01:01:21,540
‎但沒關系
But that's okay.

751
01:01:22,950 --> 01:01:24,000
‎沒關系的
It's okay.

752
01:01:27,080 --> 01:01:29,580
‎因為堅持做自己 ‎這件事本身會給人力量
'Cause there's-- there's strength in being yourself.

753
01:01:30,870 --> 01:01:31,870
‎我覺得
You know, I think…

754
01:01:32,870 --> 01:01:35,700
‎這就像攀登山峰一樣艱難
that's as hard as climbing any mountain.

755
01:01:39,450 --> 01:01:41,950
‎承認自己的脆弱
You know, I think there's bravery

756
01:01:43,660 --> 01:01:45,750
‎需要極大的勇氣
in admitting that you're not okay.

757
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:50,370
‎天吶 這真的很嚇人
Oh, God, it's scary.

758
01:01:50,910 --> 01:01:55,580
‎就像在風暴中被掀翻下船一樣可怕
It's as scary as… almost being swept overboard in the middle of a storm.

759
01:01:56,330 --> 01:01:58,290
‎并不是說我有掉下船過哦 爸媽
Not that I'd know, Mum and Dad.

760
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:05,290
‎我是杰西卡沃森
So… I'm Jessica Watson.

761
01:02:06,330 --> 01:02:09,040
‎對 我很堅強 我正在掙扎
Yeah, I'm tough and I'm struggling.

762
01:02:10,540 --> 01:02:14,330
‎實現夢想的過程雖然艱辛
And living my dream is-- is-- is hard,

763
01:02:14,410 --> 01:02:16,040
‎但我甘之如飴
but it's so worth it.

764
01:02:16,620 --> 01:02:18,330
‎哪怕在最難熬的日子里
-Even the bad days.

765
01:02:24,870 --> 01:02:26,410
‎因為這個世界…
Because the world…

766
01:02:26,500 --> 01:02:28,500
‎對 有時候它荊棘密布
Yeah, it can be a difficult place, but it's…

767
01:02:29,750 --> 01:02:33,500
‎但同時 它也美如仙境
…it's also really, really beautiful.

768
01:03:42,080 --> 01:03:44,290
‎小粉 你找到風啦
Pink, you found the wind!

769
01:03:54,790 --> 01:03:57,040
‎（北美洲-南美洲 ‎非洲）

770
01:04:10,200 --> 01:04:12,660
‎（非洲-澳洲）

771
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:38,410
‎（鮑伊號）

772
01:04:45,160 --> 01:04:46,500
‎（澳洲）

773
01:04:49,250 --> 01:04:50,080
‎你好
G'day!

774
01:04:52,790 --> 01:04:55,200
‎（澳洲少女挑戰單人航海世界紀錄）

775
01:04:59,700 --> 01:05:02,160
‎幫個忙好嗎 可回收垃圾扔那邊 ‎今天是垃圾收集日
Do you mind? Recycling's over there. It's bin day.

776
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:15,370
‎（踏上歸途）

777
01:05:17,200 --> 01:05:19,540
‎（喲：水手沃森穿越露紋角）

778
01:05:22,080 --> 01:05:24,500
‎（杰西卡沃森穿越露紋角）

779
01:05:33,540 --> 01:05:40,410
‎（第186天 南冰洋 ‎離家4892公里）

780
01:05:55,290 --> 01:05:56,290
‎杰絲
-Jessy!

781
01:05:56,370 --> 01:05:59,160
‎嗨 爸爸 本有話說嗎
Hi, Dad. Um, any word from Ben?

782
01:05:59,950 --> 01:06:01,910
‎他在他的船上追蹤你
He's tracking you from his boat.

783
01:06:03,120 --> 01:06:04,120
‎他沒事
He's okay.

784
01:06:04,870 --> 01:06:06,080
‎他只是需要點時間
He just needs a minute, love.

785
01:06:07,450 --> 01:06:08,950
‎這要不是無間斷航海
If this weren't nonstop,

786
01:06:09,040 --> 01:06:12,120
‎我和小粉一定會入港維修 毫無疑問
we would be pulling into port for repairs, no question.

787
01:06:12,200 --> 01:06:15,120
‎船漏水這情況可不是喜聞樂見的
I mean, leaking on a boat is not what you want.

788
01:06:15,200 --> 01:06:19,000
‎但只要視野清晰海況好
But as long as we've got a clear shot and an easy run back home,

789
01:06:19,950 --> 01:06:20,950
‎小粉應該能堅持住
it should hold.

790
01:06:21,700 --> 01:06:24,500
‎小粉的設計是 ‎哪怕翻倒過去也能自行回正的
Pink's designed to correct herself if we roll over,

791
01:06:24,580 --> 01:06:26,370
‎只要在沒有漏水的情況下
as long as there are no leaks.

792
01:06:26,450 --> 01:06:28,500
‎本應該也會這么說
That's what Ben would say too, I reckon.

793
01:06:29,290 --> 01:06:31,790
‎今天有很多離岸流 ‎知道該怎么做嗎
A lot of rips out there today. Know what you're doing?

794
01:06:32,370 --> 01:06:33,450
‎順應水勢
-Go with 'em.

795
01:06:33,540 --> 01:06:34,700
‎不要與之對抗
‎-Don't fight it.

796
01:06:36,120 --> 01:06:39,290
‎大海永遠比你 ‎比任何其他生物都要強大
The ocean'll always be stronger than you and every other being.

797
01:06:41,160 --> 01:06:44,290
‎若你想航海 ‎最好學會與大自然和諧相處
If you wanna sail, better learn to get along with Mother Nature.

798
01:06:45,500 --> 01:06:46,830
‎它沒有絲毫惡意
She doesn't mean you any harm,

799
01:06:46,910 --> 01:06:49,660
‎只是在做它該做的事情 ‎但有時候人類擅自闖入了
she's just doing her thing and sometimes we get in the way.

800
01:06:50,870 --> 01:06:51,870
‎來吧
Come on then.

801
01:06:52,620 --> 01:06:53,750
‎我們下海
Let's get in there.

802
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:17,790
‎（澳洲）

803
01:07:21,080 --> 01:07:25,790
‎（第197天 南冰洋 ‎離家2556公里）

804
01:07:27,450 --> 01:07:31,370
‎杰西卡 我是澳大利亞總理
Jessica, this is the Prime Minister of Australia.

805
01:07:31,950 --> 01:07:33,950
‎你也可以叫我陸克文…
-You can call me K-Rudd if you-- -Gimme this.

806
01:07:34,040 --> 01:07:36,000
‎嘿 湯姆 怎么啦
Hey, Tom. What's up?

807
01:07:36,080 --> 01:07:38,830
‎總理一直提起你
To be fair, the prime minister has been talking about you.

808
01:07:39,410 --> 01:07:40,620
‎艾米莉 你回家啦
Em, you're home!

809
01:07:40,700 --> 01:07:42,120
‎就待一周
Just for the week.

810
01:07:42,200 --> 01:07:44,370
‎我學校的人都知道你是誰了
It's crazy, everyone at uni knows who you are.

811
01:07:44,450 --> 01:07:46,120
‎我可不想當名人
-Oh, God. I don't know if I want that. -Well, then brace yourself.

812
01:07:46,200 --> 01:07:50,580
‎你繞過露紋角的照片 ‎登上了世界各地的報紙
That picture of you rounding the cape is in newspapers all over the world.

813
01:07:51,120 --> 01:07:52,790
‎大家都在為你喝彩
Everyone's cheering for you.

814
01:07:53,370 --> 01:07:55,120
‎拜托 打理一下你的頭發吧
So please start doing your hair.

815
01:07:55,200 --> 01:07:57,000
‎拜托 我只能用叉子梳頭
Oh, come on. I have a fork for a brush.

816
01:08:00,330 --> 01:08:02,750
‎大學怎么樣  ‎有在悉尼認識新的男生嗎
How's uni? Any new boys in Sydney?

817
01:08:02,830 --> 01:08:04,160
‎也許吧
Maybe!

818
01:08:04,250 --> 01:08:05,620
‎天吶 誰呀
Oh, my God, who?

819
01:08:06,700 --> 01:08:07,830
‎這個嘛…
Well…

820
01:08:08,330 --> 01:08:10,620
‎嘿 你能讓媽媽接一下電話嗎
Hey, uh, could you get Mum on the phone?

821
01:08:11,370 --> 01:08:12,410
‎馬上
Now?

822
01:08:25,700 --> 01:08:29,040
‎前方有惡劣天氣 非常惡劣 是風暴群
Bad weather on the way. Really bad. Storms.

823
01:08:29,620 --> 01:08:31,120
‎風暴 而且不止一個
"Storms," plural?

824
01:08:31,790 --> 01:08:35,700
‎是來自南極洲的氣旋 ‎規模是上次那場風暴的五倍
They're even coming right at me from Antarctica. Five times the size of the last storm.

825
01:08:35,790 --> 01:08:38,200
‎我想你可能得入港了
I think you might have to pull into port.

826
01:08:38,290 --> 01:08:41,450
‎放棄嗎 不行 做不到 ‎我不能現在放棄
Quit? No. No, I can't. Not now.

827
01:08:41,540 --> 01:08:44,580
‎-我認為你別無選擇 ‎-讓我看看天象
I'm not sure you're gonna have an option here. Let me check the sky.

828
01:08:56,040 --> 01:09:01,370
‎你為什么要這么對我  ‎就不能放我一馬嗎
Why-- Why are you doing this to me? Why couldn't you just give me a break?

829
01:09:13,830 --> 01:09:15,660
‎風暴前緣已經帶來了
The front's already generating gale force winds

830
01:09:15,750 --> 01:09:19,790
‎130公里每小時的強風 ‎伴隨12米高的巨浪
of 70 knots, with a 40-foot swell.

831
01:09:20,370 --> 01:09:24,200
‎杰西卡沃森會駛入港口 被取消資格
So will Jessica pull into port but get disqualified in the process,

832
01:09:24,290 --> 01:09:25,330
‎還是會繼續前進
or keep going?

833
01:09:25,410 --> 01:09:29,500
‎謝謝你 克雷格 ‎如果她選擇穿過巴斯海峽呢
Thanks, Craig. What about cutting through Bass Straight?

834
01:09:29,580 --> 01:09:32,160
‎她能借此抵擋惡劣天氣
It's an option, and could shield her from the worst of the weather.

835
01:09:32,250 --> 01:09:35,950
‎-以錯過第四個海岬為代價 ‎-但她能保住命 蘇西
Though she'd miss the fourth cape. But she'll live, Susie.

836
01:09:36,750 --> 01:09:40,250
‎這是我們現在討論的重點 她的生存
That's what we're talking about here, isn't it? Her survival.

837
01:09:40,330 --> 01:09:44,660
‎澳大利亞青年水手 ‎杰西卡沃森的環球航海嘗試
Australian teen sailor Jessica Watson has been confronted by another challenge in her attempt to become the youngest person

838
01:09:44,750 --> 01:09:47,330
‎再次面臨挑戰
to circumnavigate the world.

839
01:09:59,450 --> 01:10:01,660
‎你不用覺得羞恥
You have nothing to be ashamed of.

840
01:10:01,750 --> 01:10:04,540
‎哪怕最經驗老道的水手都會選擇靠岸
Even the most experienced sailors would pull in too.

841
01:10:04,620 --> 01:10:05,660
‎就連本也會
Yeah, even Ben would.

842
01:10:06,250 --> 01:10:07,200
‎朱莉
Jules.

843
01:10:08,540 --> 01:10:10,410
‎我會讓所有人失望的
Yeah, but I'm gonna let everyone down.

844
01:10:10,500 --> 01:10:13,450
‎不會有人失望的 ‎你沒看那些評論嗎
You're not letting anyone down. -Have you even seen your comments?

845
01:10:13,540 --> 01:10:14,540
‎什么評論
What comments?

846
01:10:14,620 --> 01:10:15,870
‎你博客上的評論
On your blog.

847
01:10:17,700 --> 01:10:20,120
‎-我教過你怎么看評論的 ‎-你沒有
-Told you how to do this. No, you didn't.

848
01:10:20,200 --> 01:10:21,330
‎我有
Yes, I did.

849
01:10:22,000 --> 01:10:23,410
‎好吧 打開筆記本電腦
Okay, open your laptop.

850
01:10:23,910 --> 01:10:25,700
‎點擊任何一篇博文的鏈接
Click the link on to any post.

851
01:10:25,790 --> 01:10:27,620
‎鼠標往下滾動 然后看吧
Scroll down and watch.

852
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:32,330
‎我每天早上都會查看你的最新動態
I can't wait to check how you're doing every morning.

853
01:10:32,410 --> 01:10:34,250
‎你比我認識的所有人都堅強
You're stronger than anyone I know.

854
01:10:41,120 --> 01:10:44,080
‎公有住房區有14個孩子
There are 14 children on the council estate

855
01:10:44,160 --> 01:10:47,410
‎借了我的電腦去追你的視頻日志
who borrow my computer to follow your video diary.

856
01:10:48,290 --> 01:10:51,120
‎你給了這些孩子很大的鼓舞
Oh, you are such an inspiration to these kids.

857
01:10:51,200 --> 01:10:53,450
‎我要攀登七大高峰
I am going to climb the Seven Summits.

858
01:10:53,540 --> 01:10:56,910
‎謝謝你讓我看見了 ‎這并非遙不可及的夢
Thank you for making me see it doesn't have to just be a dream.

859
01:10:57,000 --> 01:11:00,660
‎我今年12歲 也患有閱讀障礙
I'm 12 years old and I'm also dyslexic.

860
01:11:00,750 --> 01:11:03,370
‎追你的視頻讓我開始覺得
Following your videos has made me think

861
01:11:03,450 --> 01:11:07,660
‎我也能去追逐夢想 ‎有朝一日成為飛行員
that I can also reach my dream and one day become a pilot.

862
01:11:07,750 --> 01:11:11,290
‎謝謝你帶我們一起 ‎走上這段旅程 沃森船長
Thanks for making us part of your journey, Captain Watson.

863
01:11:12,160 --> 01:11:13,290
‎我回頭再打給你
I'm gonna call you back.

864
01:11:16,200 --> 01:11:18,330
‎我們眼看就要成功了
We are so close.

865
01:11:19,160 --> 01:11:20,120
‎那么…
So, so…

866
01:11:29,790 --> 01:11:31,370
‎一 二 三
One, two, three.

867
01:11:31,450 --> 01:11:34,830
‎我們愛你 杰西卡
We love you, Jessica!

868
01:11:34,910 --> 01:11:37,750
‎悉尼見
See you in Sydney!

869
01:11:43,370 --> 01:11:44,790
‎一定有辦法的
There has to be a way.

870
01:12:33,750 --> 01:12:35,580
‎我只想帶她回家
I just want to get her home.

871
01:12:44,910 --> 01:12:49,410
‎好的 我反復計算過數據 ‎還有一個選擇
Okay, so I've done the numbers over and over, and there is another option.

872
01:12:50,250 --> 01:12:52,160
‎我可以跑贏風暴
I could outrun the western storm.

873
01:12:52,250 --> 01:12:54,790
‎-不 絕對不行 ‎-本 你回來了
-No, not gonna happen. -Ben, you're back?

874
01:12:54,870 --> 01:12:57,790
‎對 杰絲 之前是我不好 ‎我不該發火的
Yeah. About that, Jess, I shouldn't have lost it.

875
01:12:57,870 --> 01:12:59,830
‎我讓恐懼戰勝了理智 對不起
I let fear take over, and I'm sorry.

876
01:12:59,910 --> 01:13:01,870
‎不 該說對不起的是我
No. No, no, no, I'm sorry.

877
01:13:03,080 --> 01:13:03,910
‎聽著 我…
-Look, I--

878
01:13:04,000 --> 01:13:07,450
‎我當時想說的是 ‎“我不是他 這也不是千禧杯”
What I meant was that I'm not him and this isn't the Millennium Cup,

879
01:13:07,540 --> 01:13:10,370
‎你不會失去我的 你休想擺脫我
and you're not gonna lose me, Ben. You're stuck with me.

880
01:13:10,450 --> 01:13:11,660
‎風暴要來了 記得嗎
Uh, storm incoming, remember?

881
01:13:11,750 --> 01:13:15,290
‎對 最猛烈的風暴會在72小時后抵達
Yeah. So the worst of the storms are gonna hit in 72 hours,

882
01:13:15,370 --> 01:13:17,080
‎如果我能穿過去呢
so what if I go through them?

883
01:13:17,160 --> 01:13:19,540
‎這不是你能硬抗的風暴
What? These are not the kind of storms you weather.

884
01:13:19,620 --> 01:13:23,450
‎我沒想硬抗 我想不用浮錨 順應風勢
No, I don't want to weather them, I want to move with them by not using the drogue.

885
01:13:23,540 --> 01:13:27,200
‎杰絲 浮錨是用來 ‎保持船身穩定的 不能不用
Jess, you have to. The drogue's what keeps the boat stable.

886
01:13:27,290 --> 01:13:30,540
‎對 但在太平洋風暴群里 ‎浮錨會拖慢我的速度
Yeah, but in the Pacific storms, it slowed us down like an anchor.

887
01:13:30,620 --> 01:13:32,160
‎對 要的就是慢
Yeah, that's the point!

888
01:13:32,250 --> 01:13:35,870
‎但小粉在上次對抗風暴時 ‎就被海浪沖擊得遍體鱗傷了
Yeah, but then we were battered by these waves 'cause Pink fought them.

889
01:13:37,910 --> 01:13:40,830
‎你說過我們不該與大自然對抗
I mean, you said we shouldn't fight Mother Nature.

890
01:13:41,950 --> 01:13:43,330
‎那我們就跟它合作
So let's work with her.

891
01:13:44,500 --> 01:13:46,120
‎讓小粉去沖浪吧
Let Pink surf.

892
01:13:46,200 --> 01:13:48,370
‎等等 她說得對
Wait, she's right.

893
01:13:49,160 --> 01:13:51,660
‎如果站在海浪前 你會被擊倒
If you stand in front of the wave, it knocks you down,

894
01:13:51,750 --> 01:13:54,080
‎但如果你去沖浪 就能踏浪而行
but if you surf with them, it doesn't.

895
01:13:54,620 --> 01:13:55,620
‎大部分時候是這樣
Most of the time.

896
01:13:55,700 --> 01:13:57,790
‎對 聽著 不使用浮錨
Yeah, look, without the drogue,

897
01:13:57,870 --> 01:14:00,580
‎你要面對的是18米高的巨浪 杰絲
you're gonna be up against 60-foot waves, Jess.

898
01:14:00,660 --> 01:14:03,000
‎所以不要被海浪沖擊
Yeah, so instead of getting battered by 'em, 

899
01:14:03,080 --> 01:14:04,330
‎而是乘浪而上
we'd ride over them.

900
01:14:04,410 --> 01:14:06,080
‎小粉體型嬌小 正好是優勢
Pink being small would actually help.

901
01:14:06,790 --> 01:14:08,450
‎小粉能撐得住嗎
Is Pink up to this?

902
01:14:08,540 --> 01:14:11,450
‎你才剛補好艙壁上的裂縫 ‎它能堅持嗎
You only just patched that crack in the bulkhead. Will it hold?

903
01:14:11,950 --> 01:14:15,620
‎況且你也筋疲力盡了 ‎而那風暴聽起來就像場馬拉松
You're also exhausted, Jessy, and the storm sounds like a marathon.

904
01:14:16,200 --> 01:14:17,450
‎我不想功虧一簣
I'm so close.

905
01:14:17,540 --> 01:14:19,330
‎嘿 別關心成敗了
Hey, don't worry about that.

906
01:14:19,410 --> 01:14:22,250
‎現在活著回家更重要
Making it home alive is more important right now.

907
01:14:22,750 --> 01:14:24,450
‎你必須靠岸
You're gonna have to pull in.

908
01:14:28,700 --> 01:14:30,660
‎我同意本的說法 安全第一
I agree with Ben. Be safe.

909
01:14:30,750 --> 01:14:32,580
‎不 穿過巴斯海峽
No! Cut through the straight.

910
01:14:32,660 --> 01:14:35,580
‎-對 我喜歡這個選項 ‎-我喜歡沖浪那個
Yeah, I like that option. I like the surfer one.

911
01:14:37,580 --> 01:14:40,750
‎-我猜你是支持“靠岸”嘍 爸爸  ‎-那個…
I'm guessing you vote for "pull in," Dad? Well…

912
01:14:40,830 --> 01:14:43,040
‎對 顯然這是最保險的…
yeah, it's obviously the safest…

913
01:14:45,370 --> 01:14:46,790
‎杰絲 我…
Oh, Jessy, uh…

914
01:14:47,790 --> 01:14:50,250
‎我不知道 我真的不知道
I-- I don't know. I really don't.

915
01:14:50,330 --> 01:14:52,080
‎我幾乎都沒出過海
I-- I barely sail offshore,

916
01:14:52,160 --> 01:14:54,790
‎可是你呢 天吶 你環游了世界呀
but you, God, you've sailed around the world.

917
01:14:56,540 --> 01:14:59,200
‎聽著 你了解海洋 你了解你的船
Look, you know the ocean, you know your boat.

918
01:14:59,700 --> 01:15:02,040
‎我相信你的判斷
I trust that you know what's best.

919
01:15:07,370 --> 01:15:08,500
‎你爸爸說得對
Your Dad's right.

920
01:15:09,700 --> 01:15:11,620
‎你是那艘船的船長
You're the captain of that ship.

921
01:15:12,950 --> 01:15:16,000
‎無論你做任何決定 我們都會支持你
We will support whatever decision you make.

922
01:15:17,500 --> 01:15:19,750
‎謝謝你 爸爸 謝謝你 媽媽
Thanks, Dad. Thanks, Mum.

923
01:15:20,330 --> 01:15:21,330
‎我愛你們
I love you.

924
01:15:22,040 --> 01:15:23,290
‎我們愛你 杰絲
We love you, Jessy.

925
01:15:23,370 --> 01:15:27,080
‎本 我的直覺告訴我 要穿過風暴群
Ben, my gut is telling me to go through these storms,

926
01:15:27,160 --> 01:15:28,500
‎不使用浮錨
and I'm not gonna use the drogue.

927
01:15:29,160 --> 01:15:30,580
‎這會是一場惡戰
It won't be easy.

928
01:15:31,410 --> 01:15:34,080
‎你需要保持冷靜 忍受疲憊
You'll need to be calm, endure fatigue.

929
01:15:35,160 --> 01:15:36,450
‎過程可能會持續幾天
It's gonna last days.

930
01:15:37,120 --> 01:15:38,160
‎我知道
I know.

931
01:15:38,250 --> 01:15:39,290
‎我能做到
I can do it.

932
01:15:40,000 --> 01:15:41,290
‎我可以的 本
I've got this, Ben.

933
01:15:42,330 --> 01:15:44,830
‎只要你自己想清楚后果
As long as you understand the consequences.

934
01:15:45,790 --> 01:15:46,790
‎我明白
I do.

935
01:15:48,790 --> 01:15:50,450
‎你說了算 船長
You're the captain, Captain.

936
01:15:53,040 --> 01:15:55,660
‎（里奇之火 ‎優質披薩-新鮮烘焙）

937
01:15:55,750 --> 01:15:57,830
‎-沃森的披薩  ‎-披薩
-Pizza for Watson! -Pizzas!

938
01:16:07,450 --> 01:16:09,950
‎湯姆 能給我們透露更多信息嗎
Tom, can we get some more information, please?

939
01:16:10,580 --> 01:16:12,450
‎湯姆 請說兩句
Tom, just a quick second.

940
01:16:13,660 --> 01:16:16,290
‎大家都準備好了嗎  ‎好的 簡要陳述一下
Everyone right to go? Okay, brief statement.

941
01:16:16,370 --> 01:16:18,290
‎杰絲會設法應對風暴
Jess will be tackling the storm,

942
01:16:18,370 --> 01:16:19,910
‎繼續嘗試成為
continuing on in her attempt

943
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:26,040
‎獨自完成無間斷環球航海的 ‎最年輕人士
to become the youngest to sail… nonstop and unassisted around the world.

944
01:16:26,120 --> 01:16:27,700
‎她絕對應該靠岸啊
Surely, she should pull in.

945
01:16:28,290 --> 01:16:32,200
‎船長已經做出了她的決定 ‎不接受后續提問 謝謝
The captain has made her decision. No further questions, thank you.

946
01:16:32,290 --> 01:16:33,410
‎漢娜
Hannah!

947
01:16:34,080 --> 01:16:36,200
‎艾米莉 能簡短聲明一下嗎
Emily, can we get a quick statement, please? Emily?

948
01:16:43,330 --> 01:16:49,700
‎（第198天 塔斯馬尼亞海岸 ‎離家2395公里）

949
01:17:05,540 --> 01:17:08,790
‎澳洲人民已然目睹風暴席卷海岸線
Australians have seen particularly terrifying storms ravaging the coastlines.

950
01:17:09,620 --> 01:17:14,000
‎而此刻杰西卡沃森的無間斷 ‎單人環球航海之旅 再經過一個海岬
The timing of the storm front is especially devastating for Jessica Watson,

951
01:17:14,080 --> 01:17:17,660
‎就能大功告成 這場風暴的降臨 ‎恐將對其航海計劃
whose nonstop, solo, and unassisted circumnavigation

952
01:17:17,750 --> 01:17:19,700
‎造成毀滅性的打擊
is one cape shy of being completed.

953
01:17:29,290 --> 01:17:31,750
‎（歡迎加入水手行列 ‎本）

954
01:17:35,870 --> 01:17:36,870
‎堅持住 船員們
Hold on, crew.

955
01:18:05,830 --> 01:18:07,370
‎我們可以的 小粉
We got this, Pink!

956
01:18:08,950 --> 01:18:09,870
‎嘿 本
Hey, Ben.

957
01:18:13,120 --> 01:18:15,200
‎等壓線越來越靠近了
Isobars are getting close together.

958
01:18:15,290 --> 01:18:16,540
‎這是什么意思
What does that mean?

959
01:18:23,580 --> 01:18:25,830
‎單體風暴合而為一了
The storm cells have merged.

960
01:18:25,910 --> 01:18:29,450
‎三個風暴前緣相遇 ‎合并成一個新的巨大風暴
The three fronts have morphed into one giant storm.

961
01:18:29,540 --> 01:18:33,080
‎我們難以想象杰西卡此刻的感受
Now, one can only imagine how Jessica must be feeling right now

962
01:18:33,160 --> 01:18:35,830
‎她即將面臨有生以來最艱巨的挑戰
as she's about to face her toughest challenge.

963
01:18:59,040 --> 01:19:01,750
‎（第201天 塔斯馬尼亞海岸 ‎離家1912公里）

964
01:19:01,830 --> 01:19:05,200
‎有一個外星人在天上等待

965
01:19:05,290 --> 01:19:07,370
‎他想過來見我們

966
01:19:07,450 --> 01:19:08,910
‎但害怕…

967
01:19:10,080 --> 01:19:12,120
‎有一個外星人…

968
01:19:34,410 --> 01:19:35,700
‎杰絲 我們都在
Jess, we're all here.

969
01:19:36,620 --> 01:19:37,620
‎嘿
Hey. Hey!

970
01:19:37,700 --> 01:19:40,290
‎跟我說說話吧 我需要分散注意力
Could you talk to me? I need distracting.

971
01:19:40,370 --> 01:19:41,790
‎我喜歡蚯蚓
I love earthworms!

972
01:19:41,870 --> 01:19:42,910
‎尼克
Nick!

973
01:19:43,000 --> 01:19:44,330
‎那個男生叫尼克
Nick, the boy's name's Nick.

974
01:19:44,410 --> 01:19:46,330
‎什么男生
Um, what boy? What boy?

975
01:19:46,410 --> 01:19:48,370
‎萬一我沒抗過去呢
And what if I don't make it?

976
01:19:48,450 --> 01:19:49,660
‎不可能 伙計
Not an option, mate.

977
01:19:50,580 --> 01:19:51,870
‎告訴你 杰絲
Hey, tell you what, Jess.

978
01:19:51,950 --> 01:19:53,580
‎只要你平安回來
You get back in one piece,

979
01:19:53,660 --> 01:19:56,660
‎我就開著鮑伊號出海到悉尼迎接你
I'll take Bowie out of the docks and sail to Sydney to meet you.

980
01:19:56,750 --> 01:19:57,750
‎成交嗎
Deal?

981
01:19:57,830 --> 01:20:00,620
‎你會出海 到海上
You'll sail? Like, open waters?

982
01:20:00,700 --> 01:20:04,700
‎對 我甚至可能會開回新西蘭老家 ‎但前提是你必須回來
Yeah, yeah, I might even sail home to New Zealand. But you gotta get here first.

983
01:20:04,790 --> 01:20:06,040
‎行 好啊 成交
Yeah, okay. Deal.

984
01:20:11,200 --> 01:20:13,660
‎杰絲 你還在嗎
Jessy? Jessy, you still there?

985
01:20:13,750 --> 01:20:17,200
‎在 你之前不想讓我穿越風暴 ‎也許是有道理的
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Yeah. Might've had a point not wanting me to do this, Dad.

986
01:20:18,080 --> 01:20:19,160
‎我好害怕
I'm scared!

987
01:20:20,700 --> 01:20:22,450
‎漢娜 我也怕
Oh. Oh, Hannah, me too.

988
01:20:22,540 --> 01:20:24,660
‎但這是我自己的選擇 對嗎
But I chose to be here, yeah?

989
01:20:24,750 --> 01:20:27,660
‎我選擇了走這一步 就絕不會后悔
I chose to be here and I'm never gonna regret it.

990
01:20:28,410 --> 01:20:30,620
‎不入虎穴 焉得虎子 對吧
Nothing ventured, nothing gained, right?

991
01:20:32,450 --> 01:20:33,830
‎（極端危險天氣警告）

992
01:20:33,910 --> 01:20:35,450
‎-不可能 ‎-什么
-That's impossible. -What?

993
01:20:36,040 --> 01:20:37,660
‎什么不可能 什么
What's impossible? What's impossible?

994
01:20:37,750 --> 01:20:39,500
‎-快告訴我  ‎-杰絲
-What? Tell me, quick! -Jess!

995
01:20:56,410 --> 01:20:58,620
‎好的 小粉 你做得很好
That's it, Pink. You're doing great.

996
01:21:27,700 --> 01:21:28,700
‎拜托 停下
Please, stop!

997
01:21:30,330 --> 01:21:32,080
‎求你放過它
Please, let her go!

998
01:23:03,040 --> 01:23:03,870
‎杰絲
-Jess?

999
01:23:25,450 --> 01:23:26,450
‎媽媽
Mum?

1000
01:23:29,450 --> 01:23:31,330
‎她的緊急警報觸發了
Her emergency alarm went off.

1001
01:23:34,200 --> 01:23:35,250
‎她在…
She's…

1002
01:23:37,250 --> 01:23:39,000
‎4點6米深的水下
15 feet underwater.

1003
01:23:49,080 --> 01:23:50,080
‎不
No.

1004
01:23:50,620 --> 01:23:51,870
‎不 她一定沒事的
No, she's all right.

1005
01:23:53,410 --> 01:23:54,410
‎打給她
Call her.

1006
01:24:01,620 --> 01:24:03,120
‎嘿 電話…
Hey, the phone…

1007
01:24:03,790 --> 01:24:06,290
‎電話在風暴中會沒信號 記得嗎
The phone loses signal in storms, remember?

1008
01:24:06,370 --> 01:24:07,750
‎只是打不通而已
-It's just the phone.

1009
01:24:08,450 --> 01:24:09,660
‎只是電話沒信號了
It's just the phone.

1010
01:24:22,290 --> 01:24:23,700
‎拜托 杰絲 接電話啊
C-C-Come on, Jess, answer.

1011
01:24:24,620 --> 01:24:25,500
‎好了
Okay.

1012
01:24:26,250 --> 01:24:28,790
‎-杰絲 杰絲 不要  ‎-別這樣 湯姆
-Jess! -Stop. -Jess, no! -Stop, Tom.

1013
01:24:28,870 --> 01:24:30,080
‎不
No!

1014
01:24:43,790 --> 01:24:44,790
‎我在呢
-I got you.

1015
01:24:49,330 --> 01:24:50,330
‎沒事的
It's all right.

1016
01:25:19,700 --> 01:25:21,040
‎-不 ‎-朱莉
-No. -Jules.

1017
01:25:21,830 --> 01:25:23,450
‎不…
No…

1018
01:25:24,660 --> 01:25:25,660
‎不…
No…

1019
01:26:55,830 --> 01:26:56,660
‎杰絲
Jess?

1020
01:26:58,580 --> 01:26:59,580
‎我們成功了
We made it.

1021
01:27:01,830 --> 01:27:02,830
‎小粉救了我
Pink saved me.

1022
01:27:07,080 --> 01:27:08,080
‎杰絲
Jess?

1023
01:27:08,660 --> 01:27:09,660
‎嗨 媽媽
Hi, Mum.

1024
01:27:11,160 --> 01:27:13,370
‎你不知道我聽見你的聲音有多開心
You don't know how good it is to hear your voice.

1025
01:27:13,450 --> 01:27:14,370
‎天啊
Oh, God.

1026
01:27:16,160 --> 01:27:17,160
‎我也是
Yours too.

1027
01:27:19,700 --> 01:27:21,950
‎天吶 你真該看看現在的天空
Oh, God, you should see the sky right now.

1028
01:27:22,040 --> 01:27:23,540
‎是嗎 很特別吧
Yeah? Pretty special?

1029
01:27:25,330 --> 01:27:26,330
‎非常特別
Really special.

1030
01:27:28,080 --> 01:27:30,830
‎你能快回來嗎 我等得花都謝了
Jess, can you come home already? You're aging me!

1031
01:27:33,330 --> 01:27:34,410
‎好
Yeah.

1032
01:27:36,870 --> 01:27:37,950
‎我想我準備好了
I think I'm ready.

1033
01:27:40,250 --> 01:27:41,580
‎她做到了
She did it.

1034
01:27:41,660 --> 01:27:43,870
‎她真的做到了 過來
She bloody did it! -Come here!

1035
01:27:43,950 --> 01:27:45,120
‎來抱抱
Come here!

1036
01:27:47,950 --> 01:27:49,660
‎你讓我們擔心死了 杰絲
You had us worried, Jessy.

1037
01:27:56,040 --> 01:27:57,750
‎-在拍嗎  ‎-是漢娜
-Are we rolling? -It's Hannah.

1038
01:27:57,830 --> 01:27:59,790
‎都準備好了嗎 攝影機就位了
Everyone ready? You got the shot?

1039
01:28:01,790 --> 01:28:03,620
‎杰絲成功穿越了風暴
Jess has made it through the storm.

1040
01:28:03,700 --> 01:28:07,540
‎沒有任何嚴重受傷或者損壞 ‎她目前正在回家的路上
She suffered no serious injuries or damage and is on her way home.

1041
01:28:12,250 --> 01:28:13,250
‎好了
-Yes! -All right.

1042
01:28:13,750 --> 01:28:16,700
‎好的 好了 各位 請離開草坪
All right. All right, all right, everyone, off the lawn!

1043
01:28:16,790 --> 01:28:18,370
‎我還指望它長點草呢
All right, I'm trying to grow it.

1044
01:30:17,910 --> 01:30:24,910
‎（第210天 悉尼港）

1045
01:31:17,500 --> 01:31:20,580
‎（杰西卡沃森 ‎歸家日）

1046
01:31:20,660 --> 01:31:24,000
‎逾八萬人蜂擁至悉尼港前灘
Over 80,000 people crowd Sydney Harbor foreshore

1047
01:31:24,080 --> 01:31:28,750
‎見證杰西卡沃森 這名女學生 ‎更準確地說 這位杰出的年輕女性
to see Jessica Watson, the schoolgirl, rather, the remarkable young woman

1048
01:31:28,830 --> 01:31:32,870
‎在出海210天后回家
arrive home after 210 days at sea,

1049
01:31:33,450 --> 01:31:36,540
‎她的壯舉讓世人 ‎看到了鼓舞人心的力量
a lesson in the power of inspiration,

1050
01:31:36,620 --> 01:31:39,450
‎這個勇敢的靈魂深深地震撼了
and the impact that one courageous soul

1051
01:31:39,540 --> 01:31:41,160
‎成千上萬的人
can have on so many,

1052
01:31:41,750 --> 01:31:42,750
‎包括我在內
including me.

1053
01:31:43,660 --> 01:31:44,790
‎來了
Here we go.

1054
01:31:45,580 --> 01:31:48,290
‎（官方終點線 2010年5月15日）

1055
01:31:49,200 --> 01:31:50,950
‎-3點33分 ‎-3點33分
-3:33. -3:33.

1056
01:31:51,040 --> 01:31:53,200
‎注意 準備播報 她到了 3點33分
Breaker, breaker, she's in. 3:33.

1057
01:32:06,500 --> 01:32:07,500
‎她成功了
She did it.

1058
01:32:09,160 --> 01:32:10,410
‎太好啦
Yeah!

1059
01:32:12,660 --> 01:32:13,750
‎杰絲
Jess!

1060
01:32:43,540 --> 01:32:45,370
‎杰西卡沃森穿過終點線
Jessica Watson crosses the line

1061
01:32:45,450 --> 01:32:48,620
‎歷經44448公里 完成了她的無間斷…
-Completing her nonstop… -after 24,000 nautical miles.

1062
01:32:52,870 --> 01:32:54,910
‎這里 快來看 看看這是誰
Here! Come, look! Look who's there!

1063
01:32:55,000 --> 01:32:56,660
‎是杰西卡
It's Jessica!

1064
01:33:56,040 --> 01:33:57,200
‎你回家了
You're home!

1065
01:33:58,040 --> 01:33:59,330
‎你真的回家了
You're really home!

1066
01:34:15,790 --> 01:34:17,200
‎有人想跟你打招呼
There's some people who want to say hi.

1067
01:34:17,290 --> 01:34:18,660
‎嘿 你做到了
-Oh! You got it.

1068
01:34:19,540 --> 01:34:20,540
‎杰絲
Hey! Jess!

1069
01:34:28,870 --> 01:34:30,450
‎-看那邊  ‎-來吧
-Look at that! -Come on!

1070
01:34:35,040 --> 01:34:38,160
‎歡迎回來 杰西卡 多么驚人的成就
Welcome back, Jessica. What a remarkable achievement.

1071
01:34:38,250 --> 01:34:40,040
‎你是我們國家的驕傲
You've done our nation proud.

1072
01:34:40,120 --> 01:34:43,290
‎你現在是澳大利亞最新的國民英雄了
You now stand tall as Australia's newest hero.

1073
01:34:48,160 --> 01:34:49,660
‎回家的感覺真好
It's so great to be home.

1074
01:34:51,040 --> 01:34:54,330
‎但我并不贊同 ‎總理先生剛才那番話 我不…
But I'm actually gonna disagree with what the prime minister just said, I don't…

1075
01:34:55,540 --> 01:34:57,540
‎我不認為自己是一個英雄
I don't consider myself a hero.

1076
01:34:57,620 --> 01:35:00,120
‎我只是一個相信夢想的平凡女孩
I'm just an ordinary girl who believed in her dream.

1077
01:35:00,660 --> 01:35:03,660
‎要完成這樣的事跡并不需要與眾不同
You don't have to be anyone special to achieve something like this,

1078
01:35:03,750 --> 01:35:06,580
‎只要找到自己的夢想 并堅信不移地
you just have to find your dream, believe in it,

1079
01:35:06,660 --> 01:35:08,080
‎為之努力奮斗就好
and work really hard.

1080
01:35:08,160 --> 01:35:09,750
‎感謝大家的熱情歡迎
Thank you for the amazing welcome.

1081
01:36:04,620 --> 01:36:07,080
‎（歡迎回家 杰西卡）

1082
01:36:09,750 --> 01:36:12,450
‎（2010年5月15日 ‎16歲的杰西卡沃森）

1083
01:36:12,540 --> 01:36:15,080
‎（在海上航行210天后 ‎返回澳大利亞）

1084
01:36:15,750 --> 01:36:20,950
‎（她在七次翻船中死里逃生 ‎經歷了逾21米高的巨浪）

1085
01:36:21,750 --> 01:36:26,870
‎（2011年1月 ‎杰西卡被提名為澳大利亞年度青年）

1086
01:36:27,750 --> 01:36:32,580
‎（盡管有閱讀障礙 ‎但她寫了兩本暢銷書）

1087
01:36:33,410 --> 01:36:37,330
‎（杰西卡至今仍是一名航海愛好者）

1088
01:46:17,620 --> 01:46:19,620
‎字幕翻譯：覃璇

1089
01:46:19,700 --> 01:46:22,450
‎（深切懷念卡梅隆戴爾）


